title: Nylabone Teething Pacifier Puppy Chew Toy
descriptions:
['Every puppy needs a pacifier to soothe teething pain, look cute, and exercise his chompers for a life filled with treats! The Nylabone Puppy Teething Pacifier Dog Chew Toy gives your brand-new pup two chews to choose from. Both have raised nubs that stimulate gums and teeth, and both cost less than replacing a chewed up pair of shoes.\xa0Designed for teething puppies up to 25 pounds - Not recommended for adult dogs or puppies with any permanent teeth.\xa0', 'Recommended for puppies up to 25 pounds only. Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.', '

                        See all items by Nylabone
']
key_benefits: ['Designed to encourage positive play and teach your puppy healthy chewing habits from an early age.', 'Keep them happy, busy and entertained while nubs help to clean teeth, reduce plaque and tartar, and promote proper oral hygiene.', "Satisfies the needs of your teething puppy with a toy that's safe and designed for pets that don't have permanent teeth.", 'Vet-recommended teething toy for puppies so you can feel confident about giving this to your pet.', 'Bright colors help keep your pet entertained and engaged.']
reviews: [I read the reviews and thought we'd be safe. We have a 3 month border collie mix puppy, and most of the reviews that this didn't work for have dogs that were bigger or better chewers, so I thought. I didn't think she would get through it as fast as she did. The pink one was chewed up in less than an hour. She really loved it, but we can't safely let her keep chomping it., I do not know how to rate this. The puppy this was purchased for is a 10 wk. old Irish Wolfhound. She carries this toy around quite a bit; however, she does not chew on it. I do not know if it is the texture or the hardness of it. She chews her other toys that are smoother and less hard. I believe that it is this puppy’s preference and nothing to do with the toy itself. That is why I gave it a three; I have no clue as to how it will hold up if she does ever actually chew it., I was impressed with the toy at first, being it is made from a hard plastic. However when I gave this to my pup, he had it chewed up in less than an hour!! I do not recommend this toy for dogs who chew on everything or bigger breed pups. I ordered this with 2 squeak toys which I refuse to give him those as I know he will destroy them in no time as well., this is the winner of our chewy haul. ordered a variety of chew toys to try out for our new puppy and so far this is her favorite. she's only 9 weeks old, and like chewing on our fingers (ouch!) this toy is just slightly softer than a normal chew toy and she loves it. having a couple toys and ring seems to entertain her more than a typical bone. will it last forever? probably not. but nice to not have puppy shark teeth attacking my fingers., I bought this toy for my 9 week old Yorkie and it seems to be one of her favorite chew toys. She's been chewing everything up and this particular toy is great for redirecting her and holding her attention. The toy doesn't seem to be worn out yet so I expect it to last quite a while., I have a 3 month old GoldenDoodle he loved this in the first few days I gave it to him and the other weeks had past and he still plays with it and it’s definitely in his top 5 he plays with most but when I was washing his toys for its weekly wash I have been noticing teeth marks on the ring and some on the toys but I didn’t think much about since there was nothing that bad on it that would choke or do something bad to him. but right now he is playing with it and it’s in pretty good shape just hopefully nothing bad happens!, This is well made, but our puppy is totally disinterested in it. I thought it would be a great chewy toy, but even when I give it to him and try to pull and entice him to play with it, he doesn't care. He goes off to find something else. This could just be my dog, I have no idea how other pups would react., Good quality. Bought this for the pup as she is starting to teeth. The toy is a little bigger than I expected but that is ok. I appreciate that there is two chewys on the ring. I put them in the freezer for awhile and then give them to the pooch. The bumpies on the chewys in addition to the cold from the freezer helps keep her interested., This is a great chew toy for our puppies! We had gone to purchase puppy chew toys at stores because we needed something right away, and the stores only had plushies and kongs! We don't use plushies because the puppies chew them and eat the bits, and the kongs were just too big. These are perfect for our 8 week old puppies to teath on and they love them!, This is one of the first chew toys I bought my pup when we got him. I thought it was cute. He loved it. So did my older pups. (the other two are 5). It's been chewed until it's just nubs and a ring. So I buy another. I'm not sure how many I've purchased but I keep buying them when they start to break because my pup (who is now a 14 month old 50 lb chinese shar pei) loves this and who am I to say no? so, yes, I know it's for teethers, but my lil' guy said he's still teething and to give him his binky back.]

title: KONG Puppy Dog Toy, Color Varies
descriptions:
["The Puppy KONG dog toy is customized for a growing puppy's baby teeth, with a unique, all-natural rubber formula that is the gentlest within the KONG rubber toy line. Designed to meet the needs of a puppy's 28-baby teeth, it helps teach appropriate chewing behavior, while offering enrichment and satisfying a younger pup's instinctual needs. The erratic bounce makes it ideal for those pups that just want to play. Want to make crate training easier or extend play time? This toy can be stuffed with KONG’s Stuff’N Puppy Easy Treat, Snacks or Ziggies (sold separately) or any of her favorite rewards like peanut butter, yogurt or kibble!", '
                No toy is indestructible. Supervise your pet when using since small parts can present a choking hazard or internal blockage. Discontinue use if the toy is damaged. Keep out of reach of children.
', 'Ships in a variety of random and fun colors!', '

                        See all items by KONG
']
key_benefits: ['Unpredictable bounce is great for energetic puppies and helps establish appropriate chewing and playing behaviors.', 'Made in the USA from globally sourced materials.', "Perfect for stuffing with KONG Stuff'N Puppy Easy Treat Paste and Snacks for longer-lasting play.", 'Relied upon by veterinarians, trainers, and dog enthusiasts for over 40 years.', 'Specially designed for soothing teething puppies’ gums.']
reviews: [I have had dozens of dogs over the years, and raising puppies has definitely been a lot easier with the addition of Kongs! There are so many different flavors of both liquid/paste based treats and solid treats that you can purchase for your pups, you're sure to find a flavor every dog will enjoy. Also, if you're on a budget, you can simply buy some peanut butter and spread it around the inside with a kitchen knife. Saves your house from teething destruction and they are also the best tool I have found for separation anxiety. Even my adult dogs get one right before I leave the house, and they don't even care that I'm leaving., Just got this today and I know it's goofy to write a review right away about an item/purchase BUT(!) I tested it out as soon as I got home with my dog - he's usually iffy about toys or anything that is NOT food... I filled it with the cheese & Bacon spray and he just went to town! Absolutely loves it. I've been thinking about getting one of these for a while but finally gave in and happy I did!, This is the perfect size for a puppy. Only complaint was I ordered pink and received blue. Puppy didn't mind but the owner gave me a hard time (jokingly). Puppy loved it and it does keep her entertained when owner needs quiet time., Smaller than I expected and I ordered a size bigger than what I was expecting. Other than that it’s good, my dog likes it as a treat. I put kibble in it, wet it, then freeze it but you don’t need to freeze it., Even as a puppy, my dog was quite a chewer. And, as most puppies do, she had absolute razor-blade teeth. She would poke holes in this and rip pieces of rubber off of it. Before it was damaged, it was really useful to cram full of peanut butter and freeze for her to get out when she was having separation anxiety., It doesn't save the fingers and hands from sharp tiny milk teeth but, Yellow Dog loves to toss it around and make it bounce and chase after it and chew on it, lol! So energy outlet wise it is a great toy from puppies!!! :D, Finally, a really tiny chew toy for my Pug puppy. She will actually be able to grab it and it is indeed softer than the standard Kong, I ordered the small as well because she may grow out of this tiny XSmall one quickly but it is the perfect starter!, This is his favorite Kong. We ordered it in blue (for a boy) . Although, when I called customer service to request the blue one, they told me they can not guarantee the color that will come. It DID arrive in blue!!, My Chihuahua/Pug mixed babies are massive chewers. Most of the items I give to them are destroyed in a few hours (or less). They love the challenge of getting their treats, and they are easily cleaned and sanitized. Hooray for me AND my babies!!!, This puppy kong is easy for my 12 lb girl to carry around and chew. I wish it was a bit shorter because she can't get the squeeze cheese or peanut butter and the end of the treat. It's really difficult to clean, but I will keep using it because it holds treats well and she loves it!]

title: Petstages Dogwood Tough Dog Chew Toy
descriptions:
["Chewing is a natural behavior in all dogs, as it helps reduce stress and can also control barking, digging or other destructive behavior. The key to embracing your dog's natural need to chew is to offer appropriate chew objects to help satisfy and relieve chewing urges. Petstages has developed innovative chewing toys designed to address chewing and dental health for each stage of your dog's development. New Petstages Durable Stick chew toys use an innovative material that combines real wood with durable synthetic material to create a stronger, safer “stick”. Durable Stick toys are sure to keep your chewing dog happy and engaged!", 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.', '

                        See all items by Petstages
']
key_benefits: ['Chew toy that combines real wood with synthetic strength, non-toxic, durable material with a natural wood smell that attracts and keeps dog’s interest for hours', 'Shape makes toss and fetch play easy, even floats in water!', 'Safer than real sticks and great for dogs that love to chew', 'Available in multiple sizes for dogs of all ages and breeds', 'Made in the  U.S.A.']
reviews: [My dogs like chasing sticks and the two of them will play tug-of-war with large sticks outside. My hound likes to chew on my wood coffee table and wood toybox when I go to work. They like this toy, but it's not their favorite. It's heavy to throw, but would be okay outside. It's very well made and good quality, so I upped my review from 3-stars to 4 because it's not the company's fault my dogs are picky about the wood they chew. From my dogs' behaviors, I'd bet that this toy tastes like wood. (I did not taste this toy.) I'm satisfied with the purchase, not sure if it's for everyone. Sometimes the dogs will gnaw on it while they're chilling on the couch, but not for long. I have a medium dog , This is much more plastic-y than woody. My dogs enjoyed chewing on them but I set a time limit being afraid it would wear their teeth too much. I have a middle-aged boxer with small teeth and lab with big teeth who loves to chew sticks. I won't buy this again. Not horrible but I really don't like the hard plastic feel. Also loud when dogs drop it on hard flooring. I think even if some material gets ingested, it seems safer than if dogs ingest real splintery wood. Pros and cons., This is a durable toy they keeps it’s shape even when the dogs are trying to destroy it. I have not had any sharp edges yet but we do get some peace’s broken off as they chew so we watch for that. The love the way it feels and gives them a good gripping surface. If you have a medium (50lb) dog I would not go smaller then the medium and would recommend leaning towards the next size up., The two dogs that visit my house regularly love these sticks. The only complaint I have is that it leaves hard little bits that I have to clean up after every chew session. i will add that I have to clean up after every rope toy or other material is played with as well. They are super aggressive chewers., Our dogs both chew on sticks like it's going out of style, but we didn't want to encourage that, especially in the house. We got them each one of the dogwood tough toys and they LOVE them!! They typically choose these over a normal Nylabone. If you have a chewer I would highly recommend this product!, I bought this for my highly destructive German Shepherd Dog who can destroy toys in seconds. We’ve had this for two weeks and it’s still holding strong. I will say that she doesn’t find the toy to be that fun, though. It’s very hard and doesn’t seem to give her a lot of satisfaction., My dog usually loves these kinds of hard chew toys but for some reason wasn’t a big fan of this one. He did chew it up but it wasn’t nearly as interesting to him as other chew toys before. The quality of the bone is otherwise excellent and a good durable choice for big chewers., Got this when my dog was smaller and it stopped him from bringing sticks inside. He’s had the same one for over a year until I just threw it away. 10/10 recommend, I’ll be purchasing another one really soon. It’s his favorite toy to chew on that he actually doesn’t destroy!!, I first tried these on the recommendation of an employee of a pet store. My lab/terrier mix would actually chew through small sapplings in my yard in order to get sticks for his chewing obsession. He loves these. They only last about a month before they get so small that I have to toss them, but most toys only last a day on my house., My 6 month old goldendoodle likes to chew, but she’s never ruined even stuffed animals. And yet... she’s been chewing on the dogwood for less than 10 minutes and it’s already starting to flake. I’m worried about her eating too much of it so I’ll have to take it away soon, which is a bummer because a. It’s more expensive than a beef tendon and lasts even less time, b. she really likes it, and c. I literally gave it to her 8 minutes ago. Thought this could help cut on some tendon/bully stick expenses and calories. What a shame. Also, it’s almost too heavy for her to carry.]

Bright colors and different textures help keep your pet entertained and engaged.', 'Keep them happy, busy and entertained while nubs help to clean teeth and reduce plaque and tartar.', "Satisfies the needs of your teething puppy with a toy that's safe and designed for pets that don't have permanent teeth and are less than 15 pounds.", 'Vet-recommended teething toy for puppies so you can feel confident about giving this to your pet.', 'It soothes teething pain, freshens breath and promotes proper oral hygiene.']
reviews: [It doesn't save fingers and hands as much from getting hurt by tiny sharp milk teeth but, Yellow Dog sure loves it! He carries it around in his mouth and chews on it! In the teething aspect it is really good for that! :D, I have a small shih tzu who absolutely loves this chew toy. Even if it's at the bottom of the toy basket, he digs through until he finds this one. If he hears anyone move this toy or shake it to play, he comes flying down the hall to join in. My small dogs can hold this toy easily and it's very durable. I buy a new one every once in awhile just because Gibbs has loved it too well - haha!, One of our Lab puppies first toys. It's really cute and was a favorite of his. He'd chew on it, run with it in his mouth, fling it and then go get it. He's 4 month old now and 30 + -lbs - too big for this toy so, I had to remove it from his toy box., My pups aren't fond of this toy. I thought the plastic would be a bit more giving so the pups could teeth and chew, but it is made of a hard material. Pups give it 2 dew claws down!, I just got a labrador puppy and I invested in chew toys. I have 5 dogs and everyone of them have played with these. They really hold up to puppy teeth and show no bite marks., My 6 month old English shepherd loves this toy so much. She will play with it by herself for 3 hours straight just rolling around with it and chewing on it., I got this because my puppy is a teething terror, but he’s obsessed with this toy! He was tossing it all around the room in excitement when I first gave it to him, and then settled right down in his spot to chew., At first my puppy preferred the softer options like the keys but those don’t last long and now he loves these!! Hold up great and it’s easy for him to hold and chew for a while., This isn’t our puppy’s go to, but he doesn’t entirely ignore it either. He just prefers softer textures to gnaw on at the moment. I think it’s just a bit too hard and clunky for him. I happen to think it look like tons of fun though!, I wish you had choice to pick the options. When I got mine in the mail it was for a power chewer. But it’s not the worst I like the look of it and it’s good for teething if you put it in the freezer.]

Designed specifically for teething puppies, this chew toy helps to promote positive chewing habits, while the unique texture is great for dental health—offering two convenient uses in one fun shape. The savory beef flavor lasts as long as the toy will, and the four textured ends help to clean their teeth and massage their gums as they gnaw away!', 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.', '

                        See all items by Nylabone
']
key_benefits: ['Non-edible dog toy is made for teething puppies up to 25 lbs who have a gentle chewing style this will soothe and discourage destructive chewing.', 'Keeps dogs busy, happy, and satisfied with its savory beef flavor throughout.', 'Made of tough, durable nylon with multiple textures for increased appeal.', 'Satisfies their natural instinct to chew and the four textured ends help to clean teeth and massage the gums.', 'Made with a comfort-hold design and recommended by veterinarians.']
reviews: [This is a great shoe for a tiny puppy in there first teeth! There’s no fear of them chewing through this. Is a good size for their mouth. I took a very light smear of peanut butter and put on the ends and it attracted our puppy to it. She often goes to it to take out some of her biting anxiety., but all in all a good chew. Pup received two (one from a friend) but she hasn't really started chewing yet. I'm hopeful she'll use this more once her teeth start really hurting., My little puppy loves chewing on this toy- it's his favorite! I think he enjoys the beef flavor more than the chicken ones. I recommend for the chewing puppies., I bought this for my Shepherd pup, but my senior terrier mix keeps stealing it for herself! Lots of chewing fun. I’ll have to get a larger one for the pup!, I purchased a different nubby straight Nylabone and our 13 week puppy chewed pieces off of it immediately. I was disappointed as these chew toys were recommended by the shelter we got her from but there is something about this particular chew toy that has been a godsend! It is very hard to find something stable enough for sharp puppy teeth but not too hard that will cause them to break creating infection. This chew is just perfect! It’s one of the only toys we can leave her with alone! The way this chew is constructed is perfect because she doesn’t focus on just one part of it helping it to last longer as though it’s 4 chews in one instead of repeatedly chewing on the same piece causing it to, My Tanzy Bell is a multipoo she wasn’t impressed with this Chew Toy hasn’t even touched it, I even wrapped it up put into freezer for short time nope still has not touched it Well this fur baby momma even made attempt to chew on it myself to convince her yum yum. I feel this item is a good product each fur baby are all different they know what they like & don’t like. Tanzy Bell her favorite is the butterfly chew toy Which Chewy does not sell anymore., The puppy likes his new chewy toy. He plays and tosses it in the air and after he is done playing,takes his nap with it. Awesome buy., when i opened the box i was overwhelmed with a terrible smell i don’t know what makes the chew toy smell so bad, don’t buy it!, Absolutely my 9 week old Golden Retriever’s favorite chew toy. The shape is easy for them keep a hold of and find an end to chew because it doesn’t lay flat., My 10 week old puppy loves this!! Keeps him busy during his teething stage! Very durable, easy to hold and good size!]

reviews: [My puppy has been chewing on this toy for at least an hour this morning in my lap and she is obsessed. I put it back in her play area with her and it is the first time she has played with a bone in her play area. She usually only bites them when I'm holding her and she plays with her other toys in her play area (notice bone behind her). It smells like chicken when holding it in hand. Cannot smell otherwise. If your dog is chewing pieces off then it is because your dog has too many teeth and this is a puppy TEETHING toy! It is meant for dogs with not many teeth. She loves this thing and I can't imagine her chewing bits off of it. She barely has teeth. She is a 9 week old mini poodle puppy., A couple of years ago I gave these to my friends puppy and, aside from bully sticks, this was their FAVORITE! I would buy one every couple of weeks and with such a low price it was worth it. Now I have my own puppy and she’s obsessed too!! So glad that it’s also beneficial for her little teeth and I can see us buying tons of these again!, I bought this for our 4month old puppy. She had it in pieces in less than an hour. She loves the bigger ones, but they are a little tough on her gums and teeth. I thought this might work better. Nope. Would work really well for teeny, sometimes, chewers, but not a bigger puppy., Got this as a gift for a friend's new rescue pup. She says the dino is saving her furniture. The pup chews on this and carries it around all day. Total win!, Love the shape, makes it very easy for puppy to hold. My husky pup is an aggressive chewer and this keeps her satisfied for at least 30 minutes., It was this or my table, this worked much better. He's just now teething and he will gnaw on this for so long every evening. He loves it!, My puppy isn’t interested in this chew toy. Too bad, he really needs it for his shark (puppy) teeth, I was most disappointed that most all toys are made in China and not USA. I try to buy USA products as much as possible. I would like to see country origin in the description. I use Chewy all the time and will continue to use but will be careful of products purchased., This is a great chew for teething pups, and holds up perfectly. My pup is done teething but still loves chewing on it and it looks like new after 3 months., My puppy went nuts for this toy. He absolutely loved it and it keeps him occupied for hours.]

reviews: [We had a Nyla bone that came in a 3 pack with a variety of Nyla bones. Our puppy’s favorite one was this one with texture so we ordered them as a replacement. It looks the same, but the integrity is TERRIBLE! It’s already falling apart after chewing for 30 min!! The last ones (we didn’t buy from chewy) lasted 3 weeks before doing this!, I haven't got my puppy yet but I have used Nylabones in the past and the dogs loved them..My pug got hold of this and was "breaking it in" for the puppy. He really liked it and he's not a puppy! I'm sure this nice soft chewy toy will be great for my little girl., My puppy is not a heavy chewier so it’s great for him, but it is not his favorite toy but he will chew on it if I have frozen it! It helps puppies with the teething process. Make sure to freeze the bone for a real treat! Do not get if your dog destroys toys easily!, My 5 month old Pomsky LOVED this petite bone. She really enjoyed biting it with back molars. After 1 month she was able to tear little pink nobs right off. I eventually found them in her stool. I don't recommend for heavy chewers., My 4-month-old corgi was really enjoying chewing on this until I noticed pieces falling off. He had it probably for about 5 minutes before I had to take it away. I personally would not recommend. Maybe not meant for teething puppies?, My dog loved it but it was easily chewed.I. can see a lot of puppies chewing right through that.I didn't read the package before I got it or I would not have got it knowing my dogs chew things up., Great for my pup who has very sharp little teeth and chews pretty aggressively. Has not been able to get off a big piece yet, and when the ends start to shred a bit I just trim with scissors. He’s been loving for almost three weeks. Much better than the flavored bones I bought from the same company which he chewed right through., Our new 4 pound 4 month old puppy is very busy chewing and playing with this bone. I recommend this for anyone with small bread puppies that are teething., My puppy loves to chew on this. He is teething and wants to bite everything in sight so this is fantastic to deter him from doing so!, My two month old puppy is HEAVILY teething and she is OBSESSED with this new bone!!! It's her favorite bone now, highly recommend!!]

reviews: [This bone is by far the best toy we’ve bought for our lab puppy! It is perfect to hide treats in and keeps him occupied for up to 25 minutes - which for those of you that know what lab puppies attention span is, is like an eternity! This is his favorite toy, in fact, he is chewing on it as I write this review! I suggest on one end put peanut butter and the other hide kibble/soft treats! Highly recommend since it also feels great in their mouths as they’re teething!, In preparation for our little ones homecoming, we bought some toys and this was one of the toys we purchased. My Alaskan Nanukklee has loved this toy since arriving home. Now as she is approaching seven months, I can honestly say this is one of the best toys we purchased! It is one of the only toys that remains in her toy lineup, and the only toy that remains from day one. We twist it, we tug it like a tug toy, I put bully sticks in it to avoid paying the high cost of bully stick holders, I stuff treats inside, or use plain peanut butter, and through all of the chewing it holds up! This toy has so many uses it’s one of my favorites for her. I highly highly highly recommend it. Just a bit of , Our puppyloves his treat bone , the treats i had on hand were to big but a little Peanutbutter works really well. This is his good boy bone or we're leaving you for a bit! Lol he also loves to just chew on it ,great for puppy teething. If you have a puppy you should add this to your list., My larger dog had a Kong bone so I got this puppy Kong for my 11 lb. Pomeranian. They both love their bones and they are the highlight of my dog's days. I just bought one for my puppy that will be coming home in a few weeks and I know she'll love it too., This has been a LIFESAVER. We also have the traditional tear-dropped shaped Kong but we like this bone version better. It holds more of the peanut butter treat and keeps our pup occupied for a solid 20 minutes if we freeze it., I purchased this item for my brown lab when he was a puppy, over a year now it’s still in one piece, he chews it everyday, he’s a very heavy chewer, anything he could get his paws on usually gets destroyed. I would definitely recommend this product!!!, Love the Goodie Bone. The puppy loved playing with it and it was the perfect size. Only reason it was not a 5 star is because I ordered pink but received blue. It was a gift for a female dog., A bit smaller than I expected, but pup loves it! We will have to get a larger one as she grows because I'm worried it could easily become a foreign body for a grown lab. Perfect size for a small breed; suits medium to large breed puppies for a time., My 4 month old puppy was chewing (and eating) many of the softer stuffed animal toys so I was hoping for something that he can chew on and not destroy. He's been chewing for an hour and has bitten anything off yet! Hopefully this will hold up longer than many of his other toys., I have a 12 week old Pitbull/ Lab and he LOVES this!! He chewed through every toy I bought him so far, but this is definitely one that has lasted. Great toy for teething puppies!]

title: Petstages Cool Teething Stick Tough Dog Chew Toy
descriptions:
['Chewing is a natural behavior in all dogs, as it helps reduce stress and can also help control barking, digging and other destructive behaviors.\xa0Freeze this Cool Teething Chew Stick and hand to your teething pup to soothe his gums, to your panting pooch to help cool down, or use anytime for a fun, satisfying, crunchy chew.', 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.', '

                        See all items by Petstages
']
key_benefits: ['Treat can be easily frozen, ideal for your teething puppy or dog with inflamed gums to help reduce swelling and numb any discomfort.', 'Crunchy when frozen, cotton/polyester fabric features lots of textures for chewers, plus soft fabric for gentle teeth cleaning.', 'Mold resistant filling is perfect for freezing and washing', 'This teething stick also helps keep dog cool during those hot summer days, just freeze and give it to your dog for an icy relief.', 'Measures 6" L x 1.5" W x 1.5" H']
reviews: [We love this toy; it’s very versatile. Soft enough to appeal when she wants to sink her teeth into something, the fins make little crinkly noises, and the shape means we can both hold it as the same time for some gentle tug. It’s as sturdy as any of the fabric toys we’ve bought, which means we’ll have to replace it, but it’s stood up better than I expected. The fin noises and bouncing ribbons on the end have been a lifesaver when it comes to distracting her from something we don’t want her sinking her teeth into., I bought this because of the teething miseries of our puppy. I had hoped it would at least be up to the quality of a wet, twisted wash cloth that had been frozen in the the freezer for her to gnaw on. It totally wasn't. I didn't find it to even get cold enough to make my hand chilly. Very disappointed. She had very little interest in it., Teething puppy is chewing on everything and this toy is pretty amazing and quickly became a favorite for my beagle. At first I worried because she chewed the bottom ribbon but the top strings get exactly where she needs them. Although full of puppy teeth marks its still here a month later!, Our puppy loves to bite and lick our cold water bottles so we thought it would be great to get him this! He likes this fine, but unfortunately still prefers the water bottles :) We were rinsing this in water and then freezing, but we discovered submerging it first in water and then freezing makes it freeze better and last longer out in the open., This toy is a favorite. My runt yorki loves to chew tags. This toy is her dream come true. My other yorki and the toy poodle fight over it too especially when its still cold from the freezer., So my puppy (Brittany Spaniel) had this toy for 5 minutes tops (that is being gracious). And it is ripped in half with the stuffing coming out and all the ribbons ripped off. This toy says it is for tough chewers but in reality it is not., My 3 mo old labrador tore all the stuffing out of this within 1 hour. So never got the chance to freeze it and test how it would be for soothing her teething., For small puppies it might be ok but I definitely expected it to be a little bigger than it was. It says in the description to freeze it for teething but it only really stays cold for a couple of minutes unlike some of the other teething toys I bought., I have a 12 week old lab puppy now and she’s had this since she was 6 weeks old. It’s been a life saver with her teething and biting. She hasn’t been able to tear it up and it’s her best friend. Thank you so much Chewy!, Got this for my teething puppy, a miniature Schnauzer, and it’s a little bigger than I thought. Too big for him to carry around, so he loses interest quickly but it helps his teething for a little so I’ll take it. Just a heads up to other buyers though that I would not buy it for really small dogs as they may not care for it]

title: Hartz Chew 'n Clean Tuff Bone Tough Dog Chew Toy Toy, Color Varies

The Hartz Chew n’ Clean Tuff Bone is a long-lasting chew toy constructed from safe and durable materials to withstand heavy chewing. The patented design supports its cleaning and tooth-scraping abilities. Enriched with a tempting bacon scent, the Tuff Bone entices dogs to exert their need to chew, while helping keep teeth and gums clean and strong to minimize the build-up of plaque and tartar!', 'Ships in a variety of random and fun colors!', 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. key_benefits: ['Provides boredom-relieving chewing action for heavy chewers and promotes clean teeth and fresh breath.', 'Irresistible bacon flavor entices your pooch to chew on the toy and not on your furniture.', "Made of soft and durable nylon that gently massages gums and helps promote your pal's dental health by fighting plaque and tartar.", 'Paw-sitively perfect for dogs of all ages, from teething puppies to senior dogs with sensitive teeth.', 'Stands up to everyday chewing and comes in a variety of fun vibrant colors.']
reviews: [My dog is a heavy chewer and was in need of a new something to chew. I picked this out and when it arrived from Chewy, my dog knew the package was for him. Anticipation was high and the recipient was trying to be patient as this Tough Bone was unwrapped. My dog took it happily, walked around with it in his mouth and would keep it within paws reach. He seeks this Tough Bone out to chew and wants to take it everywhere. My dog has never been so pleased with a gift before this one. We recommend this whole heartedly., I have two dogs, one is 35lbs the other one is 45lbs. Both love this thing so much, they had it for 2 months now and it will need a replacement soon because it's the only thing they chew! The 45lbs one is a heavy chewer and probably gives it a good 2 hours of chewing non stop every day. If you have a dog with similar needs and it's looking for something that will last two centuries, not your best option, but if you want something for them to play with and have fun, get thing ASAP., We have a 70 lb. power chewer. It seems that one of his missions in life is to destroy every toy once it is given to him. These are basically indestructible. He seems to love the flavoring - bacon is his favorite. I'm guessing the flavor wears off over time though because they will eventually get moved down the line of favorites. This is the only reason we ever need to replace them. Regardless, he ensures we get our money's worth out of them! CAUTION: I didn't notice a size indicated when I ordered this one. When it arrived, I was pleasantly surprised that it was larger than the ones we've bought at our local grocery store in the past. The larger size was great for him but would likely be , I mean, I haven’t personally tried this product, but the dog seems to really enjoy it. She holds it in her paws and gnaws at it pretty much all throughout the day. It looks like fun and I think she likes how it feels on her gums. It’s dishwasher safe but usually I just rinse it with some mild pup safe soap. The cats show zero interest so this is not one of those “cats love it too” type of instances. Wait, I take that back. They do love it because it keeps the dog busy. They can focus on napping, which from what I can tell, takes hours of concentration. In truth, this chew toy is great, my dog had surgery on her mouth for a fused jaw prior to our adopting her, and to see her gnawing and chewing, I ordered one of these in hopes it would keep my pittie occupied whom I consider a “super chewer”. It has held up well and Charlie loves it! But they accidentally sent me 6 instead of just the one I ordered so I am stocked up on these for awhile! How that happened I’m not sure but Charlie sure appreciates it., We have a 10 year old boxer who is a rescue. Toys are not high value to her AT all. We left this on the floor for our 10 month old boxer puppy but guess who is chewing away on it? You guessed it, the old one, Harper Lee! Having the best time. This works for everyone., My German shepherd enjoys chewing this bone, but I've noticed that this product flakes off as he chews. My dog then inhales the flakes somehow and I've noticed a dry cough since I've given this to him. I've taken away this bone since then., My Goldendoodle puppy absolutely loved this when I first gave it to him after he still plays with it but it’s not in his top 5 he plays with most. But I have been noticing on this toy when I do them for there weekly wash is that the little balls on the middle part tears in half. But I didn’t think much about it so I thought I could just tear it off and still let him bite it but it just kept happening more and more in the next few days and more of a choking hazard so at this point I just trashed it. But he is only 3 months old and not much of a biter, When we first got it, Daisy was smitten. She would tear around the house with this thing and fling it in the air. My dog is an aggressive chewer, but she has hardly put a dent on this thing. She has tried though., I bought one for each dog at home and they love them and couldn’t wait for me to open them! They do tend to chew the “nubby” piece off but they last for a while!]

title: Nylabone Puppy Chew Starter Kit Triple Pack Puppy Chew Toy
descriptions:

The Nylabone Puppy Starter Kit Triple Pack Dog Chew guides your pup from his first chicken-flavored teething toy for baby teeth to an active chew toy for when his jaws really need a workout to an edible bacon-flavored reward when he reaches the six-month mark. As they chew they're actually helping to clean their teeth and prevent plaque and tartar buildup.", 'Designed to satisfy the needs of your teething puppy and help discourage destructive chewing.', 'Vet-recommended teething toy for puppies so you can feel confident about giving this to your pet.', 'Made in the USA!']
reviews: [My puppy loves to destroy toys and chew. This set rocks as teeth change to adult. He now has the adult one and he loves it. It of course is chewed down but it lasts. It does leave little grainy plastic pieces on the couch and gets hair and lint stuck after being on the floor. Here is the picture of it currently. It is close to being removed from his arsenal of toys. I recommend reading Nylabone’s FAQs on when to take them away etc., Of the 3 chews in the pack, only the softest one was chewable for only one of my dogs. (both of my dogs are small to medium sized dachshund chihuahua mixes). The other 2 chews were too hard for either dog. While one dog seemed to enjoy chewing the soft "bone", it upset her tummy and she threw up the chunks for 2 days thereafter., I’ve purchased 2 of these. First time was for my daughter’s husky pup to have at our house. These helped her progress nicely and she seemed to love the flavors. Just recently purchased again for my new puppy and having the same success. Can’t go wrong with nylabones. They are a life saver!, Our puppies are a large breed and broke pieces off in minutes. However, they loved them. Just wish they were more durable. These would be great for a smaller dog or a very young large breed puppy who hasn’t developed those powerful jaws yet! They loved the flavors., My 8 week old puppy chewed the brown bone and it crumbled. I had to throw it away. I through away the other clear/brown looking one because it was bendable and knew he'd chew it up too. The bones are way to soft. My pup is a pug., My puppy will reach for these sometimes, usually only if there's nothing else around to chew on. The one he really likes is the edible one but one of my older dogs gobbled that up when I wasn't looking (oops). Would love to purchase just the edible bone again., My puppy loved the first chew bone but had nothing to do with second bone. It’s like plastic. She won’t get the third one for a little while. I hope she likes it., My daughter's little dog loves to chew... On furniture, on my toddler son's toy dinosaurs, on anything he can reach from the trash... But as long as he has one of these bones, he leaves everything else alone. Yay!, My 10 week old Bernedoodle DESTROYED the starter bone really fast. She actually managed to eat half of it. She clearly loved it, but it was way too soft for her., Like many other reviews our puppy also destroyed the first bone in under 30 minutes. Not sure what kind of puppies wouldn’t destroy it. Ours is a 6lb pup small breed. Now waiting to give the white one which I’m hoping will be better.]

reviews: [My butt kicking dogs wouldn't even touch this. I have 4. I feel like there must be a microchip in there that tells "BAD DOG" and like... reviews: [We bought this shortly after bringing our shiba Inu pup home and he has loved it since day one! Not as hard as the nylabone Puppy chews but still durable. He is not almost 5 months old and it is his favorite to have in his create or chew himself to sleep in his bed! Just wish it came in the next size up for a safer option as he grows!, We bought this toy when we brought our boston terrier Graham home 8 months ago. Surprisingly it has held up even with being chewed on daily. We just brought home another boston terrier named Mazie who is enjoying this toy as I write. Mazie takes this to her kennel and chews until she falls asleep. 1 toy for 2 puppies. I'm happy, I bought this for my chiweenie. It is way too small even for him. It looked like a toy he loves that he has, so I thought a backup would be good. This might be a good size for a little kitten., Great Pyrenees puppies are fierce little biters. Anything that vaguely looks like moms teats get nipped and chewed. It’s impossible to get them to stop, you can only change the direction of the chew. After trying a few regular rope and squeaky plush toys, I was going to give up and let her chew my shoes. But after buying this, she was IMMEDIATELY all over it. It’s a great, super resistant chew. Different textures keep her interested, and if it’s chilled it really helps her with the teething pain. She loves it! Never been so happy with a product., This is maybe good for puppies that are very, very young. My two 6month old pug puppies destroyed this instantly. I was grabbing toy particles out of their mouths., Very disappointed This is a beagle puppy not even 5 months old and she destroyed it in minutes. It was So cute, My puppy loves this toy! It is for dogs with puppy teeth and pups with some adult some puppy. It is not for dogs with all adult teeth. We have one dog (about 11 months) that comes to the house and tares this thing into pieces. It stinks because my puppy loves it! I keep buying new ones however because the price is so good!, This is Quinn’s favorite toy. She’s chewed on it since the day we brought her home. It’s a very soft and bendy texture but she hasn’t been able to chew any pieces off., I bought 2 of these for my puppy when she started teething and she liked them but they are not very durable. She destroyed one of them and my older dog destroyed the other. If you have super chewers like mine they won't last very long. I threw them both away the next day but they had fun with them for a little while., When I went to the mailbox with her to get this toy she was so excited. She knew it was for her and started chewing on it right away! She is teething so badly and this has seemed to help a lot!]

reviews: [Our oldest Shih Tzu is in live with Zukes mini bones and they have kept his breath and teeth clean for 8 years now. We now have two 1.5 year old half brother Shih tzus who seem so colpwtitive at eating things they don’t know the concept of chewing on something without swallowing whole. I just wish she would eat the bottom part as well but she is only interested in the top of the paw one hopefully she will eat the full bone., My puppy loves these toys. reviews: [I gave it four stars, because it is a great product… just WAY too big for my tiny puppy! My Maltese puppy is 14 weeks old, and just barely 2 pounds. It said the small was 2.5 in x 2.5 in so I thought that would work… but it’s 2.5 in x 2.5 in x 4.75 in! The thing is bigger than she is! She still chews the ring part, but can’t get her mouth around the actual Kong-shaped part. Watching her try to drag it over to her bed is adorable… until she has to bark at me to come pick it up and carry it wherever she wants it! LOL! BOTTOM LINE: If you have a toy breed puppy, get the original Kong puppy in XS instead! She has one and likes it plain, LOVES it stuffed with her regular dry food and some peanut, I actually need to buy two of these as my pups try and steal it from each other. They really like it and love to carry it around by the handle. They have started to chew through the handle, but so far so good., This item was described as "small", yet, in its picture-- it looks only a little bit larger than the extra small regular kong. This item is huge, and it cannot be used--especially for a small puppy!, I had one of these for my own dog when she was a puppy and bought this for a friend's puppy. Kong toys are so sturdy and this looks so cute when a puppy walks around with it. I recommend this!, Since I bought it, this happens to be one her favorite toys. If she can’t find her other 2 this pup gets this one and even sleeps with it. Words can’t explain how much it has saved me and have my pup be a happy pup., my aunt bought me this for my dogs and bought her self one for her pitbull. her pitte is very gentle but destructive when it comes to toys but this one lasted pretty long for them (about 2 days). idk why some people thought rubber would work for there big dogs but yea 2 days is great. my Maltese is very destructive and this is still holding up. we freeze some peanut butter in it and it last a while or at least long enough for me to already on my way somewhere without them knowing. I HIGHLY RECOMMEND., Works just like a regular Kong but the handle part allows a little bit of stability for them to learn to get the stuff out! We only used ours once or twice because I bought the wrong size, but for the 1 week the size was okay for my pup, she liked it! Small buyer beware I am posting on all my Kong reviews - LOVE their products, but they come in different sizes which I learned the hard way! Be sure you double check the size of all you buy and when in doubt size up!!, I usually love Kong toys as it takes my puppies a minute to chew through them (hours of puppy teeth relief!!) but this time I took it out of the box and within five minutes it was destroyed!! I am so disappointed as we have had the same product before and it took them months to chew through it. Definitely wish the second time we purchased it would’ve been better, My labradoodle loves this! Hers is pink & it has held up really well. I don’t see her destroying it any time soon., Our pup LOVES his new Binkie!! We place a milk bone in the opening and he plays with this for a long time, always successful at getting the cookie out for a treat.]

reviews: [My dog is a 7 month old chipoo. I got him this toy and he loved it. Chewed thru half of it in the first hour of having it. BUT roughly 12 hours later proceeded to puke up pieces of this toy. It is possible it wasn't the toy but there was nothing new added to his diet in the last 2 days besides this. He has currently puked 3x in the last 30 minutes little chunky spit up of this toy., He loves this chew toy so much he chewed right through one and we had to buy two more as back ups. When presented with some of his other preferred chews he will always go for this one here. He’s not 6 months with permanent teeth yet so he needs chew toys!, My puppy had it only for 2 weeks and he chewed off a small piece of it. I took it away. He is not even an aggressive chewer. Although he really loved the toy, but would not recommend due to safety concerns., The puppies love the chew toy. It is not completely hard, it has some flexibility to it, so they like to chew on it. It is well worth the investment., Winnie has not stopped chewing on this teething ring since I received it. Although she is still trying to chew up every thing else, she loves it!, My dogs almost choked to death from the Nylabone products. I threw them all in the garbage. It should be illegal. My one dog chewed pieces off that my other dog almost ate. The first one must have swallowed a piece; he kept gagging and hacking and I could not retrieve it. Almost rushed to the vet., I have a one year old chihuahua terrior mix. He has always loved this teething ring thing. Since he was 4 months old these are his favorite still. We tried so many different ones and this won. He is on his 4th. Now he chews and destroys over time quicker but at least it's his to do so with., My little chihuahua showed absolutely no interest in this or the 6 other teething rubber type bones and chews I ordered. Just a waste for me. But I love chewy. Been with them for years. They have many wonderful toys and other items and awesome customer service that is top notch. Your puppy may enjoy this it’s just my Chihuahua, Myson, did not. But he adores and has a LARGE time with the “ MR BILL- OHHH NOOO DOLL”. Have a great day. Vpmm, My Poochon Charley is going through some MAJOR teething. He is so small too. This is the perfect size for him and he LOVES it. He chews it nonstop, and it really seems to be helping him. He has almost destroyed his first one, and we are getting him another., My pup loves this bone and has become a favorite. She’s not destroyed or chewed it up yet, it’s all still intact.]

reviews: [I bought some different varieties of teething toys for my 7 week GS. I poured the squeezy liver goo into the hole. I also used treats, which she wasn't even tempted by because it was too much effort. They get stuck and are hard to get out without a pipe cleaner or chop stick.The ez squeeze was much more enticing for the puppy but she licked through it in 5 minutes until goo she could reach was gone, then ignored it. The hardened liquid would get stuck in the middle and turn gross over night. Water wouldn't loosen it so I stuck a chopstick to push it out. Just seems like too much cleaning and prep for a 5 minute relief of biting., Overall, it’s a great chewing toy.for our four month old puppy. Center cavity is too small for anything but round training treats, and even those are hard to get out. You can fill the grooves with king puppy stuff for an outdoor treat (too messy for indoors). Don’t fill the center with gooey treats. Hole is too small and Puppy can’t get them out., I can’t get my dog to play with this for longer than 5 minutes. I use it with the KONG doggy cheeze whiz spray stuff (the bacon & cheese flavor) and spray the stuff inside the crevices of this toy. He likes it, but honestly, he’d much prefer to chew on a chunk of apple. It is a good toy for chewing, and when he does have interest in it, he seems to be having a good time, but it’s definitely not a favorite. For the price, I’d still recommend it for a puppy, so I’m still going to give it 4 stars., My puppy definitely is drawn to this more than his other toys. Kept him occupied for like 10 minutes the first time he got it. Which in puppy time is forever. Just wish we could pick the color of it since pink isn’t his favorite, Our chocolate lab received this today and 4 hours later he already taking small pieces off the toy. He loves it & I can tell it's helping his teeth, but this type of toy is better for small breed dogs & not big dogs since they have a stronger jaw/bite. So sad it didn't work out, because I could tell it was helping his gums & teething well. The marketing should be targeted to the little puppers. It's a good toy for the appropriate size dog., Great chew toy and my pup loves it. I’m just sad that I could only use it for like 2 months before my Great Dane pup out grew it. I was scared she would choke on it so I had to take it away. It’s a great toy, I just wish they had a bigger size for large breed puppies., I was pleasantly surprised when this came today. I haven’t had a dog that liked chewing on rubber toys but my puppy seems to really like this one and thankfully it came in blue. I’m pleased that he can’t destroy this toy and it’s a good size for my Yorkie puppy., My puppy seemed to be interested in the odd shape. He has played with it several times but just prefers to chew on it. It holds up to all those puppy teeth!, Love Kong products, good quality plastic for chewing! These are fun if you have the patience to stuff things into the little grooves, but takes a really long time to do that. Pup likes it and will play with it when I give it to her, but rarely will pick it up on her own, I think because shes not sure what to do with it! Small buyer beware I am posting on all my Kong reviews - LOVE their products, but they come in different sizes which I learned the hard way! Be sure you double check the size of all you buy and when in doubt size up!!, My Golden loves this! It was an impulse purchase, but my 5 month golden loves it! I'll put some peanut butter in the groves and she will be entertained for 10 minutes easily!]

reviews: [Buster is a 90# Olde English Bulldogge and he has destroyed many "tough" toys... in very short order. He is very proud of himself when he can chew off a corner or a little piece. I got this toy to help clean his teeth primarily as well as to satisfy his chewing urge. Had the toy about 10 days now and it is holding up well. has just enough flexibility that he can't get an angle on it to bite off a chunk. He really likes this toy and also wants to play fetch and take away with it. Thanks Champion ! Buster and Mike, I have a bull terrier puppy (6 months) that chews on everything. It has been hard to find toys for her that she likes AND can't destroy easily. She loves this toy. She chews on it for hours at a time. The only thing I don't like is she drools like crazy when chewing it, but that is not the toys fault. LOL, I ordered two of these and was happy to see they gave me to different colors. They are lightweight so the dogs can toss them up in the air a little bit which adds to their delight when playing with them. So far they have seemed to be fairly tough, holding up to their heavy duty chewing., I bought this wanting to help Gurus dental teeth cleaning. Just brushing his teeth wasn’t working well. Thankfully he really took to the toy which was a big relief. He loves bitting it and playing with it on his own. He also enjoys playing fetch with it and I love putting treats in it for him to figure out how to get. It’s a bit challenging for him, but I love that it keeps him occupied for extended times and he does manage to get all the treats out most of the time. So overall this is a 3-in-1 excellent pet-approved owner-approved toy. I’m super thankful for it! I haven’t had any issues where he bites through the material, but we’ve only had it for a little less than a week. Perfect for bored, I ordered this not really knowing how my dog wld respond she has rubber squeaky toys that she's never touched but I thought if worse came to worse I could always give it to one of my sons dogs who both live her as well. But to my surprise it was one of her favorites. She's an 8mth old Rott & when she sees the chewy box arrived she jumps around like a child on Christmas morning ☺️. It's hilarious & she just kept going back & fourth between this & the jolly ball I had just bought., This is a great toy for large dogs. Our boy 1.5 yo loves his toy. I love it because sometime I put little training treats in one end and he just plays and it makes it extra special, The item said it was heavyweight! NOT!!! My dog is a chewer.I know this. That"s why I look for heavy duty toys. But come on One hour I expect at least a days worth of chewing before I have to throw the item away.I may as well take my money and toss it in the thrash., The hard thick rubber and heaviness is better for a big dog. I have a 36 lb Frenchie and he can barely pick it up but he drags it and chews it right up! Lol, I have a very aggressive chewer , so I am limited to what I can get her. So far this toy has held up very well and she loves it., I received the toy in purple (the color is shipped randomly). I have a two year old Cane Corso/Red Nose Pit who is an aggressive chewer. I played fetch with him with the toy and in between throws he was happily chomping away at it. Within 20 minutes he had bitten off pieces of the toy. Some toys don’t even make it past the 5 minute mark– I have to buy very durable toys for him. I had hoped this would be one of them but it was not. I guess my “champion chewer” is a bit too powerful for this toy!]

reviews: [My dogs liked the toy and, as chewers, it seems to be holding up well. I took off one star though because it makes a mess if you add dog toothpaste. They licked it some, rolled the gorilla around on the floor, and then repeated it all over the place so I spent a fair amount of time cleaning up the toothpaste off the floor and dog beds. They had a blast making a mess with it though! I’m not sure it makes a difference for their oral health but it’s worth a shot., My dogs love to chew and are very aggressive chewers so I bought this as a house toy for them to chew on under supervision but neither of them like it at all, it has a very strong smell to it. Money wasted on this one. I should’ve just bought another kong stick., My dog loves toys and destroys toys(bull terrier) she chews this gorilla then spits it out. So I think she gets a taste of baking soda that she doesn’t like. This works o.k. For me, I always watch them with toys because I don’t want them to tear up and ingest the things. But it is so nice to have one that doesn’t get destroyed and doesn’t go under the furniture either., My 45 lb female German Shepherd mix really enjoyed chewing this toy. However, when my male 80 lb Anatolian Shepherd got a hold of it... game over lol! He ripped chucks off of it like it was nothing. So if you’ve got a big doggo like me, I would choose a different chew toy. However, it worked great for my medium size girl!, My dog was chewing up everything, I have had this gorilla for almost a year and it is still in almost new condition and it is my dogs favorite toy! This is an outdoor dog and I recently got a pup and saw them playing tug with it. I think it is great!!, Our dog was mildly interested in this when I would put treats in the dispensing cavity but it was so small and deep into the treat that my dog was unable to get even the smallest training treats out, leaving her frustrated and me having to dig my finger in to fish them out before they start rotting and stinking. Great idea but the execution needs some work., For my 6 mo pup, this toy is too heavy for her to run and carry and she doesn’t chew on it often, but I think when she does the grooves help her teeth? Also, only put tiny treats in it or you’ll never get them out!, Our girl Jeep, a little cattle dog mix, loves this toy so much as a chew, for catch and as a little pal. I have multiples for back just in case ..., I have tried other Kong-like toys with my husky but she never bothered with them. I’ve had this toy for about 7 months now and she plays with it every single day. I did have to cut some of the prongs shorter so her treats come out. She throws it around the house every night, regardless if there are treats in there or not. She doesn’t really chew on it like other reviewers have mentioned. After 7 months the toy looks untouched, it holds up so well! This is literally the only toy she plays with now!, My dog loves chewing on this. He likes to chase it due to its erratic bounce and then accidentally drop it and it starts all over. So far minimal damage on the toy but chewing hasnt been his sole focus. I would not get it as a treat dispenser it is nearly impossible to get them out even with fingers. I might try and put in a bully stick type treat and see how that goes. It does have a very strong odor that hasn't gone away but doesn't seem to bother my dog and the humans have gotten used to it.]

reviews: [This is the best toy for my dog who has some anxiety when we leave the house. I stuff it with turkey jerky and push it toward the middle of the inside of the toy - really tight. She will take it, chew the ends, roll on her back and hold it with her two paws in the air to see if something will fall out. It keeps her super busy and motivated as we walk out the door. It is always empty when we get home. It's her favorite toy. I like to give it as a gift too., This began to crumble in my dogs mouth within the first few minutes of play. It wasn't the result of aggressive chew, rather, the result of a defective product. You can tell because it started to break off in smooth geometric patters rather than his teeth-shape. I'm really disappointed in this and for the first time EVER, the KONG brand., I got this thinking it would last as a toy for my bullys to play with during the day while they are out side and I’m doing chores. within the first day they had it tore up. I purchased 2, because I have 2 lab mix rescues and within a day they both had chewed the ends off. I was afraid they would swallow the pieces so I took them away from them. Guess I need a tougher toy. These might work for smaller dogs or not aggressive chewers., Was very disappointed with this KONG toy. My pup had it for no more than 10 minutes when the rubber started flaking off into tiny pieces. I guess this toy isn't intended for dogs that are chewers? Bummer since we have really liked all other KONG items we have purchased, I got this toy for my fury kids. It's very challenging and keeping them occupied for a long time. However, the combination of the shape of the toy and their hard-working saliva attracts almost everything on the floor and carpet. Each time when they play with this toy, I need to wash it thoroughly to make sure nothing is inside and out. Otherwise, its a great concept!, This Kong seems to have gotten a bit sturdier since we bought the same one a few years ago. This is probably a good thing, since the old one succumbed to my dog's modest chewing. He works a little harder on this one to get his biscuit out -- also a good thing., So maybe my shepherd lab isn’t a genius, but it’s so tough to get treats out of this thing! The only way is for your dog to chew hard on the toy which breaks up the kibble/treats, while the fall out the sides in tiny specks that you have to vacuum up later. I tried shoving a rawhide bone in there which kept her entertained for a long time (and even left bite marks on it), but the bottom was so stuck it eventually took me prying the soggy thing out with a spoon. Solution: on one side I cut one of the flaps off, and now it’s perfect. She can roll it and flip it around and eventually food will come out without her losing interest., Did not last even 5 minutes. I never even had a chance to put treats in it. My pup destroyed this toy! Power chewers beware it will not hold like the actual Kongs do. Very disappointed in this king toy. Should have looked through more of the reviews., This is huge and extremely durable but not for aggressive chewers. It took awhile but our dogs started at hole in bottom and worked from there. They love the toy however. If it was a solid piece I don’t think they could destroy it.]
