reviews: [Great purchase for our pup. We like to stuff it with small treats and give it to her in her kennel when we leave. It keeps her much more distracted than her regular puppy Kong with peanut butter in it. This is also great for her to just chew on. We'll have to get them pretty regularly as she really love to chomp on it., Our puppy loves to try to pull her rope toys through the hole of this tire toy. We pull the rope toy out and she will pull it back through. We can keep her occupied for hours this way. She also loves it when we roll it across the floor. She takes off after it and slides across the hardwood floors., My dog is obsessed with this toy. I opened the box and threw it to him. He has enjoyed rolling it. It fires perfectly in his mouth. Sometimes it gets stuck in his mouth but it stays interesting. It’s definitely his new favorite toy that staying interesting for an active puppy., This is my senior yorkies new favorite toy. It’s the perfect size and is soft, which is good cause she’s missing teeth. I got lucky and was sent a pink one which is what I was hoping for., Our pup absolutely loves this tire toy / it keeps him occupied and is one of the best toys for puppies. It’s easy to hide treats in the tire and they’re able to retrieve them instantly - it also feels great for them as they’re teething... As you can see from the pic - the choice was simple!, So I bought this for my male husky and I thought it was ganna come in blue but it needed coming in pink the dog really enjoys the toy so that’s why I have it a 4 star, My puppy loves to chase this toy when I roll it. I show it to him when he starts chewing on things or biting., I bought Kong thinking it is the toughest for puppy chewing. To my surprise the lab pup murdered his new Kong Tire in less than an hour. Odd we have a black Kong tire & it is fine. So not sure what happened to our new blue one., Easier to get the treats out than the traditional Kong so does not keep the pups occupied as long but they like playing with it., We have all of Kong’s puppy line rubber toys because we love the brand, but the tire is just ok. It’s nice to fill with wet food and stuff in the freezer but our puppy can’t ever get any more than half of it out. It is also somewhat hard to clean.]

title: Busy Buddy Bristle Bone Treat Dispenser Tough Dog Chew Toy
descriptions:
["It's a doggy dentist's favorite tool and a doggy's favorite chew… all in one! The Busy Buddy Bristle Bone Dog Toy has nylon bristles and rubber nubs that stimulate the gums and remove plaque and tartar as dogs entertain themselves gnawing and chewing trying to get their hard-earned reward: rawhide! Bristle Bone Dog Toys are available in multiple sizes and include 4 treats.", 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.', 'For Refill Treats:\xa0Click here', '

                        See all items by Busy Buddy
']
key_benefits: ['Durable nylon and rubber construction, includes 4 Busy Buddy treat ring refills', 'Comes with all-natural rawhide treats', 'Nylon bristles and rubber nubs that stimulate the gums and remove plaque and tartar', "Made using compressible rubber that's perfect for medium-strength chewers", 'Available in multiple sizes']
reviews: [Chevie is a 95 pound Boxer/Mastiff mix and a strong chewer. While the "bone" part held up well, she was ripping the rubber part out so she could get to the treat discs. Tonight, a piece of the rubber got stuck between some teeth. Took us a little while to figure out what was frustrating her and to dislodge that rubber. We've had to take it away from her after only 3 sets of treats., The toy was great until it broke/jammed. I am disappointed with the product, as it no longer unscrews to add the treats. I even used a vice to attempt to unscrew the end, but it is jammed beyond belief. This toy should last longer than 6 weeks and this specific product my be defective. I'd recommend it if your product is not defective like mine., I'm impressed with this toy! While I can't say I'm crazy about my 9 pound dog eating rawhide, I can say that he is busy and focused for about an hour or two in order to get the rawhide pieces out. Also, he has to take the rawhide off in such tiny pieces, I haven't seen any digestive issues yet. And again...focused and busy for an hour or two. :), My dog really likes this chew toy. I have to say that I’m very glad it is dishwasher safe as it gets a little disgusting once she’s chewed on the treat rings. I bought a second type to alternate while one is being cleaned. I do soak it before going in the dishwasher. Gypsy enjoys the peanut butter flavored rings best. I gave it four stars because, after being chewed the bone edges get wrecked, and tend to collect fabric debris, which is difficult to remove., I think this is a great toy. Especially with bristles that help brush teeth. I got small and ordered small treat to refill. WRONG!!! You need size B to refill treats and that would be a medium not a small size. Maybe I didn’t read throughly enough. But ultimately figures this out on amazon., My medium size Jack Russell mix chewed the white bristles the second time he had it. Now there in no cleaning of his teeth without the bristles and I am afraid he swallowed some of them. I used it with the purple and the chewed white but it just isn’t working well now. I wouldn’t recommend this product. I got the large ball for my lab and so far so good., my dog absolutely loves this toy! i've bought her so many toys over the past two years and this is always her go-to! we've had this toy for about a year now and it's taken quite a beating but it still works and it is still her absolute favorite! the treat rings also keep my dog busy when she's bored or when i need a break. currently purchasing a new one because she loves it so much :), My dog is a 10-year-old Gordon setter. She’s not a crazy dog but she enjoys chewing on squeaky tennis balls but she doesn’t tear holes in them. She destroyed this within a month. Chewed some of the parts of plastic which started to fall apart. She loved the little insert discs that taste like rawhide. But this did not last long and she’s not that big of a chewer., bought two because I was so excited, and extra refill treats for future. Both dogs were very excited at first. The problem was they were able to get the chewable part of the disk, the replaceable one, town just partway and then I would have to unscrew it to give them the rest. And then the second problem was one of my jobs which such an aggressive chewer, that actually broke. Which left me with tons of leftover disks that I just fed the dogs as treats. While looking for more interactive toys for the dogs, I realize how important these reviews are and decided to fill it out., My big red healer eats bones this size all the time. This thing is too hard. The dog actually lost interest and opted for her rubber toy. The food rings should have been much larger where they could at least get at the actual treat to have a reason to continue trying. I give this 1 star because she at least liked the ring treats out of the bag.]

title: Nylabone Puppy Chew Chicken Flavored Puppy Chew Toy
descriptions:
['"Oh boy! My first chew toy!" Sure, puppies can't speak, but the tail wag says it all. The Puppy Bone Chicken Flavor Dog Chew Toy from Nylabone is recommended by vets as a pup's favorite teething toy. The chicken flavor keeps them coming back instead of looking for less vet-recommended objects to chew - like couch cushions, pillows, and brand new shoes. Nylabone Puppy Bone Chew Toys are made in the USA.', 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.', '

                        See all items by Nylabone
']
key_benefits: ["Designed to encourage positive play and teach your puppy healthy chewing habits from an early age. It's got a chicken flavor that's sure to be a hit with any pup.", 'Keep them happy, busy and entertained while helping to clean teeth, reduce plaque and tartar, and promote proper oral hygiene.', "Satisfies the needs of your teething puppy with a safe, softer material that's perfect for pets that don't have permanent teeth.", 'Vet-recommended teething toy for puppies so you can feel confident about giving this to your pet.', 'Made in the USA!']
reviews: [My dog is a boxer/hound. 63 lbs. He is technically a super chewer, but the hard bones make him bleed. This was the perfect solution and the chicken smell is much stronger than the white version of this bone (adult version). Since it is softer, he can break it much easier, so I don’t leave him alone with it as he breaks off nice size chunks that he could swallow. Won’t last as long as the adult version, but he prefers it and it has paid off much more in terms of how often he goes for it. He prances around the house with it and looks for it everywhere when he cant remember where he left it last., 2 stars because my puppies went to town on these as soon as I gave them to them so I know they like them but didn’t last 10 minutes. Bought these for our two 4 mo old lab/boxer puppies. Thought it would be good because description says for “puppies” and sized for under 35 lbs which they are. Until now they have been chewing soft toys but wanted to give them something harder for their teething. Had to take them away so they wouldn’t swallow the pieces. Very disappointed and wasted money. Probably ok for smaller dogs just not my big puppies., I got this for my 2 4 months old beagles who are going through their teething stage. However, the knuckle got chewed off in about an hour and had to take it and throw it away. I do not plan on buying this again since it didn't stand up to them. But I did give it 2 starts because they did like it, it just didn't last long enough for them and for my wallet., My puppy is 7 months old and a huge chewer so I thought this Nylabone would be perfect. Within minutes he knawed a huge piece off the end and when I read the warning that pups should not consume the chewy I was worried. I tossed the puppy chew away and will be mindful to maybe move him to an adult chew toy., Extremely disappointed with this item! I ordered this for my one-year-old who loves chew toys. Literally within MINUTES he destroyed this bone and was swallowing the small pieces that broke off! Terrible product!!!, This bone is too soft and can be shredded in no time by most dogs. And since it's for puppies, they're going to want to eat the pieces that come off. This really needs to be safer if its meant for puppies, its so easily destroyed with chunks coming off., My 3 month old American bully tore right through this in 2 days. He had a similar one but it was just smaller. Not a bad toy just better used at a very young age to prevent destroying the toy., My 10mo lab chew thru this bone today and we just got it in the mail! She got large chunks off and Definitely ate some. I thought this would help her all a sudden chewing phase but now i must return to the drawing board. I would not recommend for large dogs., My puppy went right to this chew toy out of several that I purchased together. Hes only had it for a few hours and has got a good start on chewing it up. See picture., My 12 week old goldendoodle chewed through this bone within minutes and swallowed the pieces that were chewed off. Later that night she was vomiting up large pieces of the bone that she swallowed. Very scary and would not recommend!]

title: Outward Hound Triple Jack Squeaky Dog Chew Toy
descriptions:
["Introduce your pal to a toy that's sure to be a blast with the Outward Hound Triple Jack Chew Dog Toy! This exciting toy offers multi-sensory play and features a fun, unpredictable bounce. Are regular toys just not stimulating enough? The Triple Jack is made with three different squeakers and lots of different textures, bringing new fun to your canine companion. No matter which end your dog chews on, she'll be met with a surprising and silly sound! This toy grunts, squeaks and squawks and is sure to entertain and engage.", 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.', '

                        See all items by Outward Hound
']
key_benefits: ['This multi-sensory toy is designed to engage pups with multiple sounds and textures built in.', 'Each end is constructed to feature different chewing textures that will keep your pup engaged during chew and playtime.', "Different squeakers make different sounds, so your canine is met with a variety of fun noises—whether this toy is grunting, squeaking or squawking, it's three times the fun!", 'Fun indoors and out, this dog chew toy bounces in unpredictable ways, making toss and fetch more entertaining.', "Great for pups bursting with energy, Jack offers multiple types of stimulation and may help satisfy your pup's natural instincts."]
reviews: [When I received it, the green squeaker was broken. So not a bop. Then as my dog played with it, a 20lbs blue heeler, each squeaker would break 1 by 1. She still plays with and loves it without a doubt. 3 of the squeakers still work and it's been about a month since she got it. It's a little tough for her to squeak because she goes ham on her other squeak toys and its super annoying, so I'm happy it doesn't squeak so easily and gives her a challenge. It's a great toy for sure other than the easily broken squeakers., This is my puppy's 2nd favorite toy! Next to the Petlou plush Bunny. Because of its odd shape it takes unexpected hops which thrills her. She also uses it as a teething treat. My only concern is that I just noticed she is nibbling off little pieces and eating them. Surprising because it is quite durable but she is a wild 4 1/2 month old pit so I suppose it is to be expected., I’m always searching for new toys that will keep our rambunctious bulldog mix occupied, and this one does the trick! He loves the unpredictable bouncing pattern when I throw it, and he loses his mind with the different squeaking sounds that it makes while he’s got it in his mouth. I left off one star because after a short while most of the squeakers don’t seem to work anymore, but my dog still loves this thing. I would order again., Our Kane is a lab mix and LOVES to chew. Was very hopeful this toy would keep him busy. He took his new toy from me while I was breaking down the Chewy box for recycling. Got back inside the house and there were pieces of pastel plastic everywhere...it was like someone broke open a pinata full of plastic in the living room!! The squeakers are right on the end of each piece and those were gone before I picked up the last of the plastic. Great if you want confetti, not so much if you like a clean living room, My pup immediately loved this toy, it’s an interesting shape and has 3 different squeaks which he is a big fan of. Unfortunately, he’s a professional chewer and was destroying this toy within the first day of getting it. He definitely is enjoying it, but it will be a short lived play item as he breaks it down and the squeaks no longer function... Would recommend this toy if 1. Your dog is smaller/doesn’t tend to destroy toys via incessant chewing or 2. You don’t mind a shorter life span as long as the pup is having a good time while it lasts. :), I can't believe how long this toy has lasted..it's been almost a year since we got this for our Golden Retriever puppy. He has destroyed many other toys but this one still survives. It has a fun bounce and different squeakers. The squeakers don't work so well anymore but it still bounces and he still plays with it., I have two power chewers that have destroyed lots of toys. They love squeaky toys but usually they are only good for limited play before they are destroyed. This toy is 2 weeks old and STILL has the squeakers working!, My Mini Aussie Loves this toy so much he takes it to bed with him. Very tough material as many of his toys only last 1 day. I highly recommend this toy if your dog loves to fetch and chew..., My 4 mo old puppy chewed off pieces of the rubber within minutes of chewing it so we took it away. Two of the 6 squeakers didn’t work when it arrived. Not a good toy., My Plott Hound adored chewing this item and to listen to the squeaking sounds it made. It took four days to completely demolish it. Not made for a big time chewer, but it is enjoyable to chew!]

This Puppy Twin Pack includes a soft plastic Puppy Bone for teething puppies before they get any permanent teeth, and a Dura Chew chicken-flavored bone for powerful puppy chewers and puppies starting to get their permanent teeth.', 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff.                         See all items by Nylabone

key_benefits: ['Designed to encourage positive play and teach your puppy healthy chewing habits from an early age. Chicken and Allergen-free Peanut Butter flavors are sure to be a hit in any household.', 'Keep them happy, busy and entertained while helping to clean teeth and reduce plaque and tartar.', "Satisfies the needs of your teething puppy with a softer material that's perfect for pets that don't have permanent teeth and are less than 15lbs.", 'Vet-recommended so you can feel confident about giving this to your pet.', 'Made in the USA!']
reviews: [My little one has decimated these, he loves them. He really likes to chew so these have been great to keep him chewing. I have tried other brands and they go unused., When I ordered these it said Bacon Flavor. When they arrived one was chicken flavored and one was peanut butter flavored. My puppy doesn’t like the chicken flavored chews., My puppy LOVED this toy. I put it in the crate with her for something to chew on. I think it was chicken flavored which made it all the better. She chewed one of the ends off and I couldn’t find it anywhere. She ate it, thankfully ended up throwing it up, otherwise would have ended up at the emergency vet. I’ve gotten rid of all the nylabone products and switched to more durable toys and rawhide., My foster puppies haven't quite figured out what these toys are, but they are a good price., I'm not sure why but my pup refuses to gnaw on this bone. I've pretended like it's my favorite thing in the world, pretended to chew and lick it, she just doesn't care for them., Since these were small for puppies, I bought them. Neither one of the puppies will play, chew, or have anything to do with either flavor of these Nylabones. I would not recommend unless your pet/pets are used to nylabone type toys. Then they might like them., He loves these! I have one in his crate and the other in our living room and he loves to lay in his bed and chew them. I’m sure I’ll buy them again when they need to be tossed., I orginally bought these for my 6 year old aussie who loves to chew but has a hard time doing so! They worked great for her, but worked even better for my 7 week old German shepherd! Hes chewed on one for hours and it's tough enough to withstand his puppy bites! 10/10, I'm very disappointed in this product, within minutes my puppy had this is little pieces I had to throw it away before he swallowed them., I got this for my miniature poodle who is currently teething and she’s really picky with everything. Surprisingly, she loves it. I highly recommend this. Great purchase and great price.]

title: Nylabone Puppy Twin Pack Petite Ring/Bone Combo Puppy Chew Toy
descriptions:
['Made from softer material to satisfy the chewing instinct of teething puppies and encourage non-destructive chewing. Bristles raised during chewing will help clean teeth and prevent tartar build up. Designed for teething puppies - Not recommended for adult dogs or puppies with any permanent teeth.', 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.', '

                        See all items by Nylabone
']
key_benefits: ['Designed to encourage positive play and teach your puppy healthy chewing habits from an early age while discouraging destructive chewing. This twin pack of chicken flavored chews are sure to be a hit with any pup!', 'Keep them happy, busy and entertained while ridges and nubs help to clean teeth, reduce plaque and tartar, and promote proper oral hygiene.', "Satisfies the needs of your teething puppy with a toy that's safe and designed for pets that don't have permanent teeth and are less than 15 pounds.", 'Vet-recommended teething toy for puppies so you can feel confident about giving this to your pet.', 'Made in USA!']
reviews: [My 5 1/2 month old Shih Tzu loves this. For some reason she still hasn't gotten all of her adult teeth yet, but Vet isn't concerned about that as it took longer for even her baby teeth to come in.She will gently chew on it to help her gums. My 3 month old with a mouthful of baby "needle" teeth tries to steal it from her.. they are hilarious together!, My 3 month old Golden retriever is teething, and we've tried several different Nylabones, benebones, and bully sticks to satisfy her need to chew. Everything has been too hard for her to really get into it. The "starter" bone of this packet is almost slightly rubber-ish to the touch, and it was the perfect amount of softness to get her want to chew. As I type this, she's laying down and chewing away, which is a first for us. I wish I had found this sooner and saved my money trying out other products, We needed something for our new 3 month old puppy Zoey and this bone has been great for her teething, My 8 year old cocker stole the easy chew Nylabone from my puppy and consumed it. It was not supposed to be eaten and a warning was on the package. Now I'm waiting for it to pass. (At least I hope it does)., my new 14 week old German Shepherd puppy Max loves chewing on these items. Better them than my hand, Butters, my 10 week old puppy is loving these teething bones. The are just a tiny bit soft and small which is perfect for easing the teething pain. I bought one for each room of the house so if she starts to chew on something that isn’t appropriate, I’ll just switch it out for her., I choose Nylabone products for all my dogs chewing needs. They offer a variety of sizes and chew "strength" which is very important. I have 4 dogs that all have their own bones.... This particular item is just sturdy enough for my little guy and just the right size... He's only 7 pounds right now!, We bought these knowing we were going to be bringing our furbaby home. She loves them!! She wanted to bite on my fingers as puppies will do and I just slipped this to her and she picked it up and went and laid down and chewed on it. She is loving both of them., I originally bought them for my new pup Lola as she loves chewing on everything. She liked them both for a little but then Beaker discovered them and took over. He's a hard core chewer and these stood up to him which was great! I would recommend them for pups that chew on things, not just teething pups., We got these for our very nippy Pomeranian puppy. He’s not very interested in them, but I figured out if I freeze them he LOVES them! We freeze these and it seems to really help his teething. So 3 stars because on their own he really didn’t much care for them, but 5 stars because they freeze nicely.]

title: KONG Ring Dog Toy
descriptions:
["Help your dog spend his boundless reserves of energy with the KONG Ring Dog Toy. This long-lasting chew toy will provide hours of playtime for you and your furry friend. It’s made from all-natural red rubber, making it erratically bounce, zig-zag and hop on the ground when thrown, engaging your dog's natural chase instincts. The ultra-durable ring toy has added nubs, so your dog will enjoy chewing, while also helping him support his healthy teeth and gums. Plus, it’s an interactive way to spend more time with your best friend.", 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.', '

                        See all items by KONG
']
key_benefits: ['All-natural red rubber ring toy, built for long-lasting engagement to keep your furry pal happy, busy and entertained for hours.', 'Designed to encourage positive play and teach your puppy healthy chewing habits from an early age while discouraging destructive chewing.', 'Nubs help to clean teeth and reduce plaque and tartar while promoting healthy teeth and gums.', 'The rubber toy is a great way to have more interactive fun with your pal—just flick it and let your furry best friend try and catch it.', 'Withstands hours of fun whether it be out in an open field or at the beach.']
reviews: [I have power chewers in my household and they can defrock any toy leaving it a sad little pile of itsy bitsy pieces within moments of laying tooth to it. I got this toy because Kong toys tend to last a lot longer than anything else that isn't constantly policed usually being lost rather than destroyed. Somewhere beyond my back fence where the deer ticks and red bugs roam is a fortune worth of Kong toys. We're going on a couple of months now and the toy has held up really well against hours of daily rough tug of war and chewing. Its large enough that they can comfortably tug of war with it and it throws well but doesn't have quite the bounce of the regular cone shaped Kongs we get so it has not, This ring, while on the smaller side for a 90lb boxer mix, still performs up to task. He's a power chewer and can destroy most toys within minutes. However, this one he either isn't really trying or it holds up that well. It is a little small to use for tug of war without putting my hand in (unintentional) harm's way. But overall, it's one of his favorite toys and we are both pretty happy with it!, Kong toys are the go to toys in our house. The dog seems to enjoy most of them. The ring toy she will chew on for a few minutes but quickly becomes bored with it. Not my favorite either. For an intense chewer the choices are limited it has held up well though.Most toys only last a day or two and this one like other Kong toys has been a task for her to destroy. She has not succeeded in chewing it up., Our dog Lucy loves this chewy ring. She growls at it, throws it in the air, and catches it, then runs all around the living room rug with it. Sometimes I think it's calming for her to sit and chew on. She's a power chewer and this ring holds up really well against her sharp chompers!, My beagle pup did not care for this toy at all. As hard as I tried to get her engaged with the toy she didn’t care for it. It seems sturdy and resistant but I think it’s too expensive for a dog having no interest in it., Our two-year-old Airedale is crazy about this ring. He is a champion chewer, and the Kong rubber is one of the few materials that can stand up to his jaws and teeth. He also enjoys carrying it around in his mouth and compressing it., We bought this as a replacement for a similar nylon ring toy we routinely were replacing as it got chewed up and little bits of plastic kept coming off. We worried she would eat the plastic so we’re looking for a similar alternative as she loves the ring toys and has a powerful chew. Luckily Kong had this and it had been working wonderfully since! It’s a similar rubber to the classic Kong dispenser toy and can withstand our pups chew sessions with no damage. Also love that we have peace of mind now with her not having to swallow and little pieces by mistake!, This toy was a little smaller than expected, but that's my fault for not checking the dimensions in the listing. I got the small/medium one for my little 5 lbs dog. I definitely wouldn't give this to a medium sized dog, despite the small/medium size description. 15-20 lbs would probably be the largest size dog I would consider giving this to. It's made out of the same sturdy rubber other red Kong toys, so it should work well for mild-moderate chewers. I wouldn't give this to a hardcore chewer however as it probably wouldn't hold up. My dog wasn't really interested in it, but she's also VERY picky about her toys, so it's no fault of the toy. I gave it to a friend though who has a small dog as, My pup loves kong toys and this is great for something different. It's shape means we can play tug with it or even throw it like a rather heavy frisbee. She can often be found carrying it around in her mouth., This is a good strong rubber however the sizing is deceiving. I purchased a large and thought it would be a good size for my 6 month old puppy. She chews through everything. It is a great toy but to small. I will purchase again in a extra large. However I do recommend this for a medium size dog. My dog is 60 lbs at 6 months old. Knowing Kong toys I thought it would be the best size for her. This is the only Kong she likes. Her other Kong toys she doesn't have much interest.]

title: Nylabone Chill & Chew Freezer Chicken Flavored Dog Chew Toy
descriptions:
['Delicious, easy to fill, and ready to freeze, the Chill & Chew Freezer Chicken Flavored Dog Toy from Nylabone is an exciting treat that your four-legged friend will love to chomp. This cool (and cooling!) toy is made with a soft, durable material that is perfect for gentle to moderate chewers and features an inner reservoir for freezing. Fill your Chill & Chew Toy with water or your buddy’s favorite spreadable snack before popping it in the freezer for a long-lasting treat that stays chilly through long chew sessions. The unique textured design helps to reduce plaque and tartar, while the irresistible chicken flavor keeps your pup chewing away even after it thaws.', '

                        See all items by Nylabone
']
key_benefits: ['Softer material is ideal for more moderate chewers.', 'Fill with water, chicken broth, peanut butter or other freezable snack for tasty, long-lasting fun.', 'Unique texture is designed to help clean teeth by reducing plaque and tartar.', 'Infused with chicken flavor that your pup will find irresistible!', 'Proudly made in the USA.']
reviews: [My 5 month old Goldendoodle absolutely LOVES this toy. She’s going through her teething stage right now (poor girl) and chews on this with almost the same amount of excitement as a bully stick. It’s pretty durable so far; the material is holding up but it’s not too hard for her puppy teeth. It looks like a little doggy ice tray and it doesn’t take very long to freeze. Wild recommend!, I wish they made a bigger one or with deeper holes but he loves it and so do I! I put some yogurt into all 5 holes and freeze it. It keeps him busy and he loves his yogurt. title: KONG Senior Dog Toy

key_benefits: ["Perfect for stuffing with KONG Stuff'N Senior Easy Treat Paste and Snacks for longer-lasting play.", 'Made in the USA from globally sourced materials.', 'Made with a soft, all-natural rubber formula designed for seniors.', 'Erratic bounce re-establishes play and exercise in mature dogs.', 'Helps reduce boredom and relieve separation anxiety for senior dogs.']
reviews: [Great toy. My little dog (10lb chi-pom) has a hard time getting in the middle of the toy so wish it was a tad shorter or that it wasn't 100% hollow so he could get to the PB a little easier. However, love the bounce - he has fun chasing it around! Smells super bad, really hope it's not toxic. I would be more comfortable with a toy made out of something safer. He doesn't seem to mind it, but I worry., I have a 9 year old Chihuahua mix and I can't remember the last time she played with a toy. She just doesn't seem interested. Plus her age has affected her teeth and gums. Hard things can sometimes cause her gums to bleed a little. I bought this because I recently purchased a large classic Kong for my puppy and one day I turned around and my Chihuahua had it in her mouth packing it off to steal the treat inside. I thought I would buy her her very own more suitable one. She doesn't do much chewing on the toy itself so far but she absolutely loves to get treats out of it. Very glad I bought this. And I do have hope that it may reignite her long lost love for toys., I did like it, but my dog have a hard time with the smell of the kong. It took him a little while to want to try it. He likes is now, since it has been cleaned a few times, and the plastic smell is not so strong any more., We adopted a “senior” dog, and this Kong too was a lot smaller than I expected. It was more squishy compared to the regular red Kong, which I would expect for a senior toy, but the size was a bit disappointing., Our puppy has now destroyed two kongs, she literally chewed the top off from a puppy one and a large one. We sent kong an email an photo's but have heard nothing back from them. We have used this for years with other dogs and k-9's we had., my dogs love this when i fill it with peanut butter and freeze it - they love chasing it and licking the filling as it melts. i have to get another one so they don't fight over it!, My Beagle loves this toy, she's a puppy. I hide treats inside. I love the playtime this toy brings to her. Thank you, I bought this for my 5 month old lab puppy who is a very soft chewer so the regular kong he wasn't interested in but this one he likes. It's softer, but i'm not saying it would be good for all labs it depends on your dog as I've had some labs that were pretty strong chewers. Kongs come in different sizes so there's several to choose from., Ok, so I have a 13yo rat terrier and she can be stubborn an has really never like toys. At first she didn't like it, kinda just looked at me like I'm crazy even tho it had peanutbutter in it. I then put her fav treats w/ the peanutbutter an tried to hype her up an it worked! Just gotta work with some fur babies, It’s a struggle to get my dog to eat out of a bowl! I bought the senior Kong hoping that she would enjoy it and man does she!! She will even eat her dry food! She loves it so much and has gained weight back! I definitely recommend this if you have a picky small senior dog like I do!]

reviews: [I'm a big fan of this antler-type dog chew. One of my dogs is a big chewer - the other doesn't chew on anything at all, including this bone - but I love this for my strong-jawed chewer. I wouldn't have bought it at full price because it's a gamble what my dog will actually like., We have a 10 month old lab mix powerchewer/shredder. He destroys all his toys. reviews: [Our two year old Lab chooses this over every other toy in the toy box. Hands down, best purchase we have made for him. We play fetch every day. I believe that it would be very durable but she just is not that interested in it. When I put treats inside, she goes nuts trying to get them out but they are impossible to get out. I think it would be a good chew toy for an aggressive chewer but not great for treats., I thought this would be more like a throw toy but it's very thick and wide. It does roll well. Yeah, finally a toy he didn't chew up!, Love the material of this toy. Soft yet strong. It is hard to get all the water out of the inside of the tire after washing. reviews: [I love buying this toy for my 10lb maltese and my 60lb Am. Bully mix. They enjoy chomping on the nylabone part and then get the satisfaction of gnawing on the ball for ages. This toy really is one of the toughest toys I've ever purchased! You have to make sure you get the right size for your dog because that will make a huge difference in durability. I buy the small for the maltese and I get the XL for my am. bully and and it's lasted against the bully's LOVE and obsession of chewing. The only reason I've had to replace is because my big dog got the little dog's and annihilated it. Definitely keeps the dogs busy!, I have been looking for a rawhide alternative for a while now. My dog loves rawhide but as he has gotten older and bigger it is harder to find rawhides that last. He is a year old and only 55 lbs, and a medium sized rawhide bone used to last him a few days. Now they are gone within one sitting. It has just become too expensive to maintain his rawhide habit. I was pleasantly surprised that this chew bone - armed with two little rawhide rings - kept him occupied as long as it did. The rings lasted about 10 - 15 minutes, and then he played/chewed on it for maybe another 5-10 minutes - long enough to let us eat dinner in peace. Given what I was paying for rawhide bones this is a tremendous value, I bought this toy because some one recommended it and oh my goodness i am glad I bought it my dogs love it so much I might have to buy more of them, My dogs seem to like these toys, but be aware that the size "small" for this is not the same "small" as other Busy Buddy Toys and requires a smaller treat disc. Size small for the bone is size A treats whereas size small in the bristle toy is a size B., Oliver isn’t quite sure about this. He likes it once he gets started but he’s not quite sure exactly what to do with it. And he hasn’t figured out how to chew on the bone and not just the discs. He’s a rescue, still learning how to be a dog. Hopefully this helps!, Just bought this product and my miniature doberman pincher takes him five minutes to get the treats off. After that he's not in interested in it, He loves this chew toy. Especially when attaching the treats to it. He's had it for a few days now and the toy is a tough one! I'll be getting another when the time comes!, Our dog loves the treats you put on this toy, but we have to replace it every 3 months or so. He chews the ends so much that it is difficult and eventually impossible to put back together., This is great for heavy chewers. It also is fun with just the ball separately. He did find a way to quickly get the chew treats off though. Sometimes we just put one treat on., This is a very strong toy. Nani loves it so much she won't let the other dog near it. She usually destroys everything and this one has lasted and kept her busy. Love it!]

reviews: [This bone feels like it’s made of super hard plastic, there is no give in it at all. My dog grabbed it, tried to bite on it for about 10 seconds, and left it alone. There was just nothing interesting In It for my dog. It might work for yours if it has a super strong bite..., I have tried this product in regular, mesquite, large & medium. My dog just does not chew on it much, doesn't care for it much. I don't feel like there is much flavor in this so called mesquite version. I will not buy any versions of this product again., He tends to want to chew on sticks outside so this was a test but. He loves it and choose in it all the time. I love the big size so it will last longer. I bought two at the time so ai have a back up for later when this dwindles down., Our puppy is teething like crazy and traditional chews just don’t seem to interest him. He’s been eating black stained bark and thinks it’s a jolly game being chased around with them in his mouth. This chew is safe, satisfies his need to chew and is two paws up! @baloo.the.adventure.pup, My 24 pound dog chewed on this for about 15/20 minutes and when I looked at it, it was shredding away. I don't want my dog to eat this, I wanted him to just enjoy chewing. I won't let him chew on it anymore., Gave it to my lab puppy when she was 4.25 months. She LOVED it. It is the perfect hardness for her. It's soft enough so she makes dents in it, but not so hard she has given up on it. She is fairly fussy with toys. This has kept her interest the longest of all the toys we have given her., My Cardigan Welsh Corgi has very little interest in nylon or rubber chews so it was hard to get her to chew anything that wasn't edible. These Dogwood toys are a hit! She has always loved to pick up sticks at the park or on a walk so I'm grateful to have an alternative. She's a moderate chewer and I'm buying a replacement just now after 6 months (disclaimer: they've really gotten me through most of her puppy teething as she's 9 months old now). The pieces that have broken off have been VERY tiny pieces; it hasn't been messy (we do have a roomba) and I can't even see them in her stool. She also hasn't thrown up., I watched my dogs having a lot of fun with this chew toy. It is great for cleaning teeth because it lasts longer than most others., My almost 2 year old Boston Terrier loves to chew so I thought I'd try this one since it was BBQ flavor which was a new taste for him. Well he loved it but in less than 5 minutes he had chewed off big chunks which were laying all over the couch and could be choking hazards! He's never done this with any of his other chews before. This chew is a big no from me and had to be pitched., My pittie/GSD mix loves the original Dogwood stick, so I knew she'd go nuts for the Mesquite flavor. She loved it, but unlike the original, this Mesquite version seems to crumble and break off much more easily. She must have ingested quite a bit the first and only time she chewed it, because she woke up early this morning and vomited the most I've ever seen her throw up. Sure enough, all the reddish brown pieces were there in her vomit, and later that day, in her #2. I recommend the original Dogwood stick, but not this one.]

reviews: [Welp, chalk this up on the tally marks of toys our 10 lbs chihuahua mix can destroy in a bathroom visit. Her favorite game is tug-o-war and she doesn't let a day go by that she's not whining to play with this toy. Stella's crazy strong and I am in much better shape having her and playing several times a day. I can say, & Stella would agree, this thing really stretches and doesn't break! When I'm exhausted & our playtime over this gets put up out of reach!, Very durable and stretchy, my dogs love fighting over it, and since it’s not a stuffed toy there’s no Worry of fluff going everywhere if they break through it, I have a 70 lb Pit and he loves this toy. reviews: [I am giving this product one star. While it is a great idea, it is very poorly made and put together. It has a yucky odor to it. key_benefits: ['Scrubbing grooves promote gum and tooth health by reaching up to the gum line to scrub off plaque and tartar.', 'Nubs work to stimulate the gums and remove any leftover food debris for optimal cleaning.', 'Baking soda infused for the cleanest and easiest dental care, all while your furry friend plays.', 'Made from super tough nylon to withstand even the most aggressive of chewers.', 'Delicious mint-flavor will keep your pooch happy, healthy, and kiss-ready.']
reviews: [I bought these T-Rex chews as a Novelty... colorful toy with a novel taste. I thought maybe, what looked to be neat fun to me,might be – Bleghh, Yuck, Ewww!! – ignored by my daughter's heavy chewers. Or a T-Rex could be reduced to unidentifiable chunks & bits of green... but I took a chance. ....... — COPPER – her Rottweiler Mix ‐ AND — PENNY – an American Bull Terrier – will tear chew toys to bits in just days. After a week of hours each day of chew-play, they love them and they're still fully intact........ — These Denta-Saurus Chew Toys appear to be just as tough and durable as described. Their bright green, minty fresh, colorful appearance make them attractive...... — ..... —— , I would recommend this ONLY if you have an aggressive chewer. It is made of very hard plastic, unfortunately thats the only thing that lasts for my pups. It has lasted a whole week so far, it looks rough and beat up but there are no big pieces that come off it like the rubber chew toys(looking at you Kong!) All in all a decent toy and the pups love it, Great for active chewers. Didn’t realize there were size recommendations, or I would have ordered a larger size for my 60 pound boy. He’s tough on chewers. 4 instead of 5 stars because after a few days he chewed off sharp fragments that he started to gag on. Will try larger size next time., This toy is terrible. It is too hard for either of my dogs to chew. The toy almost feels as if could shatter if I threw it on the ground. It could probably break a tooth., Bought this on a wimp in order to meet the minimum for free shipping. Turned out to be a GREAT purchase. Both my Australian Shepherd and my American Bulldog LOVE this toy., My Cane Corso puppies absolutely love these dinosaurs. They are very durable for pups that love to chew, My pup loves this toy! Of all of the nylon toys she has, she’s been loving this one the most. The one take back from this toy is that it doesn’t last very long when it comes to the wear of the product. She has been chewing it nonstop the last three days and the nose of the alligator is almost completely flattened. But she still has plenty of other parts to chew like the tail and legs. And it is minty so you can smell it on the pups!, My boxer absolutely loves it. Very cute chew toy ., Why would even an "agressive chewer" want to chew on ceramic. This Denta-Saurus is as hard as glass with glass texture. It may smell like mint but was useless as a chew toy. No, I do not recommend this...maybe a planter ornament? a waste of money., we were surprised how much the dogs liked this. it's pretty hard, but that makes it durable. our dogs destroy 'tough' toys in minutes, so this was a pleasant surprise.]

reviews: [Our dog is working on the end nubbs and chewing them down well even though it is really a hard bone. We have LV wood floors and when he drops the bone it is so loud it can be obnoxiously loud. So just a heads up during movie time depending on your home flooring., Bought big one for my pit bull and small one for my chihuahua. They both go for big bone so I guess the small one ain't good (even tho its the same thing). They are both heavy chewers so I highly recommend it., The 3 stars are not for the product itself but my dogs disinterest in it. As far as the product itself we see no issue. She just doesn’t care for it. We have a dog with Ehlers Danlos and an abundance of energy but unfortunately due to hips popping out of joint and a hip surgery can’t get exercised enough to relieve most of her energy so she turns to chewing on things. We thought this would help as she’s an aggressive chewer and she wouldn’t tear it up in one chew session, but she chewed away for a few minutes and that was it. Now it just sits there ignored. We’re not sure exactly why she doesn’t like it., Looked at the size chart before ordering and I ordered the petite because it said it was 6 inches and it is not it is only about 3.5 inches. Size charts are either wrong or misleading, I'm not sure about the "Beef Jerky flavor" as it doesn't have any kind of scent, but my dog loves it, chews on it a lot, and it seems like it's going to last for years so I guess that's all that matters., My dog has shown absolutely no interest in this item. This is our dogs go-to toy when his teeth start to hurt. reviews: [My deaf dog can only hear a few noises like (lucky me) squeaky toys. So I was sure that she'd look adorable playing with this toy. However, the toy doesn't squeak and my dog subsequently found it very boring. I've tried getting her to play with it but she seems convinced that I bought it for myself. It seems well made, though who thought that making the tail pop-able was a good idea?, I bought this because my dog gets so bored with toys quickly. I wasn't expecting a whole lot but turns out my dog LOVES it. He also likes to tear holes in his toys, so I was expecting this one to last a few days before being destroyed. Well it's probably been about a month and it doesn't even show signs of wear and tear! Definitely recommend, This was one of the toys I picked up when we were going to get a dog and one of the first she really loved. It took a few months, but she ended up tearing it apart. She loves it so much I am getting her a new one., My dog enjoyed this toy however I wish it was just a little tougher, thicker. It lasted a couple of days but once major sections were torn out, he abandoned it. Toymakers if you’re listening, we need some thing like this that’s a little tougher but not as tough as the really hard chew toys. That is your challenge. Do you except? Lol, Ordered 2 of these, one never worked at all, no squeak at all and the second one worked for about 10 minutes, called customer service and am still waiting on replacements. Will see if they work., The is a soft rubber toy. I like these better then the hard rubber because my pups chew them to bits. Soft rubber..no problem., I have 2 50 pound+ dogs and they love this toy! We have had it for over 2 years and they haven’t torn it up!, Among all the items in this order, this is the only item I am disatisfied with. The sqeaky has no sound. Only air comes out of it when pressed.We did not give it to my dog for fear that it would get frustrated. I would like to return/replace or a refund for this item. Please let me know how to proceed., Our Bulldog loves this Duck!!! She jumps on it,chews and still is holding up to the Bulldog challenge!!!, I love and my corgi loves this toy. The only bad thing is the loud squeak so no playing at night as we are in an apartment. It's bouncy, easy to fetch, and he loves just chewy on all the different texture.]

reviews: [My rescue dog, Shadow is an extremely spoiled and pampered little furry boy. He has more toys than Santa and all the elves together but his absolute favorite is the Dura-squeak ball from Hyper Pet. He takes one of them with him everywhere he goes, include to bed!! There are other balls that are the same size and squeak - but he can tell the difference and just won't have it haha. He's out of the phase where he demolishes every thing he put his mouth on - thank goodness!! But he never chewed up one of the Dura-squeak balls - They're pretty tough or maybe it was because he loved them so much. All I know for sure is I'm going to keep him supplied with the little green balls! Without them he goes, We were gifted a toy almost identical to this (purchased from a chain pet store) about 5 years ago when our oldest dog was a puppy. She didn't chew on it a lot so it was still intact when we got our new puppy a year ago. He is a very aggressive chewer and the original toy held up for an entire year. I just replaced the original toy with this one thinking it was the exact same but there is definitely something different in the way it is made because he destroyed it within 5 days. I think this toy would be great for a dog who is not an aggressive chewer., The "Unpredictable bounce will have you pup entertained for hours" statement is misleading. I ordered the stick, not the ball, and it hardly bounces on my hardwood floors. The item's description needs to be amended. This thing is not bouncy, and definitely not unpredictable., Within 30 minutes of getting it out of the box...my 6 month old 30 pound puppy chews it to the point where the ends pop out. I do not recommend. I bought this because we got the ball a month back and its AMAZING....but not this DON'T WASTE YOUR MONEY!!!, This is one ball that isn't too heavy or tears apart easy for our 20 lb. dog. He loves to play with it and fetch it. The squeaker doesn't last long but our dog still enjoys it. It's better than a tennis ball because the lint from a tennis ball would bother our dog. This ball is easy to rinse off too. We wish Chewy still made it available to order., Received in the mail today....I was gone 4 hours and my mini dachshund destroyed it before I got back. (Thankfully he was with my parents and they took it away), Apparently not durable enough for the jaws of a husky, mine ripped it to shreds in literally ten minutes after I gave it to him. Oh well, back to searching for another., We keep them outside and that’s what we play fetch with. Our pitbull goes crazy for the squeaky inside and they hold up pretty good to the sharp teeth and the heat and cold temperatures., One of puppy's favorites. She took it to her crate day one for a good knaw. It squeaks (not an easy task) and bounces pretty good gives puppy a good scramble but small enough she can trap and carry. Love this one!, I’m calling this the Pac-Man ball because it’s come across at one of the seams in just 30 minute of ball playing and it now looks like the mouth of a Pac-Man. The balls I thought were great, have failed. This one was one I was hoping would replace the chuck it ultra squeaker for my girl, hoping it would hold up longer... sorry to say it hasn’t. So tired of wasting money, with money I don’t have to waste!]

Highly recommend for chewers., Our Rottweiller/Mastiff mix, Chip and Chocolate lab, Stella LOVE this toy! They play fetch together every morning and this is the only toy they want. I plan to get another one soon., I have two large breed power chewers who can destroy most toys very quickly so I didnt have too much hope for this toy. reviews: [It’s important to know that this toy is not for tough chewers, the rubber just isn’t designed for that. However! This is amazing but make sure that if you are getting it for a puppy that is going to get bigger then I suggest getting the size they will need when they are full grown or at least a couple sizes bigger then they need now., It was hard for me to locate a chew bone where my dogs wouldn’t eat the plastic. I will purchase more and feel confident That they aren’t eating it., I got the medium size thinking it’s be bigger than small size but it was not, the medium size is ment for dogs under 25lbs definitely not for my pup. I don’t even think the large size would have been big enough for her., It’s pretty sturdy. I ordered the medium but it looks like a small to me. If you’re thinking of ordering the medium, I’d order the large instead., I was way more excited than my Boxers were about this toy. I ordered 2 of them and gave one to each. They looked at me like...what's this for? They had zero interest in this toy. Both of them!!! Maybe it needs to smell yummy to them or something, but they haven't been touched since we got them., Sadie (my Maltipoo) loves this toy. key_benefits: ["NewHide has none of the uncertain swelling properties of rawhide, but all the taste your pal couldn't get enough of.", "Braided ends create a varied texture, creating a durable chew that won't bore your fur baby.", 'Specifically formulated to be lead and phthalate-free, so you can be proud to serve your pup this alternative.', "Made in varied sizes, ranging from petite to large, to make sure there's one for every pup—from the smallest mouths to the busiest biters.", 'Proudly made in the USA, with quality control reining over everything—from the ingredients to eye-catching details that you and your dog can recognize.']
reviews: [We recently adopted a 5-year old lab mix who does like to chew some, on sticks and plastic frisbees. She has had no interest in this bone whatsoever - it was one of our first buys for her, when we thought she'd need to be kept busy while alone. But it has very little texture for her to sink her teeth into, and really just feels like the smooth plastic of a fold-out table. I have tried to entice her by smearing peanut butter onto it, but there is no interest in attempting to actually chew on it. It's been a waste of money for us. But will give it to my in-laws who have a younger dog., My 35 pound Australian Shepard/Corgi broke one end off within a day. After that we just kept finding little chucks of this everywhere. Had to throw it away., We’ve been happy with other Petstages products, but as other reviewers have explained, pieces of this get everywhere when your dog chews it. These also do not last nearly as long as other Petstages chew toys. My lab mix chewed half through it in less than an hour, so I had to take it away from her to prevent her from eating/destroying the whole thing at once. It may be fine for casual chewers, but not for strong, persistent ones., Our German Shepard and American bulldog mixes love these bones. We keep them on hand at all times to occupy the boys. The chew is substantial enough to withstand the 80 pound Shepard’s aggressive efforts yet has a more forgiving firmness than antlers, etc. that our veterinarian advised against after the bulldog broke a molar. NewHide does not present the risk of indigestible rawhide chunks. The bones do shed tiny crumbles, which may be a con for some pet parents, however they vacuum up easily. We are fans of this pet product and have gifted it to other pets in the family., This is what the bone looked like after 48 hours. By 72 hours later, it was a tiny nub. I didn't want my dog to choke or totally swallow it so I tossed it in the garbage. She chews a lot, so if your pup chews heavily, I do not recommend this bone., My 9-year old Havanese/Corgi mix loves this chew toy. I didn't give it five stars because of the shavings that come off when he's chewing. Hopefully this is not something that will get in his digestive system and cause issues later down the road. Overall, satisfied., My lab mix promptly took this bone when I gave it to him and proceeded to carry it around from room to room all morning searching for a place to bury it. He's tried digging in his crate, his bed, and the couch but was ultimately unsatisfied with these options. Finally,he found a crevice between the wall and a storage bin that he slipped the bone into and pushed further in with his nose. He has yet to chew on it but it made for a good mental exercise! He hasn't done this with any other bone before., Although my dogs loved it the toy only lasted 2 days in my house. It did break into many little pieces I had to vacuum up unlike most of the others I have bought. But was as described and would be more suitable for a more moderate chewer than aggressive., I do not recommend these bones. I have a doberman and a boxer. Both dogs chewed on the bones some but it made their mouths bleed. The bone is like hard plastic. My dogs chewing on the bone made it have sharp points/edges. I had to throw the bones away after a couple days. These bones are nothing like rawhide., I thought I'd give this a try too see if this was more durable than the nylabones we usually get for our dog. Hes seemed to like it right away but not 10 minutes in he had those white shavings, everyone is talking about, all over and was starting to choke on them. Needless to say I took it away and tossed it. He's not a super strong chewer either, so I was kind of surprised. We usually love the toys he gets from Chewy, but I would not reccomend this one.]

title: Planet Dog Orbee-Tuff LED Strobe Ball Tough Dog Chew Toy

Best of all, this patent-pending technology involves absolutely no glues or adhesives, making this ball 100% non-toxic, and 100% safe. reviews: [Planet Dog Orbee tuff balls are the only ones that last with my 2 German Shep/Lab mixes. They still tear them apart, but it takes months not days. I purchased the Strobe ball just for fun along with a squeak one. The dogs were curious with the strobe in the dark, but as hard as they are on toys, the strobe only lasted a few days. The ball is still in good shape to play, just doesn't light up any more. For dogs that are not hard chewers, the light would probably last longer., Not sure that my dogs were impressed by the strobe affect or the bounce but the neighbor dog seemed to like the lights. Too bad the strobe lasted less than 3 hours of play. Put it away while still working but pulled it out today and dead. It's a great concept but they need to come up with something that won't die after such a short time. They still like the bounce but they also love their other rubber bouncy ball that's a bit cheaper. Would I buy this again for the little bit of extra money that this costs just to have the lights? Not sure since I didn't see them any more excited over the lights than a non-lit ball. They're still puppies so they're amused by virtually any toy so perhaps, My 9mo is about 75lbs and DESTROYS most toys. This ball has lasted through his incessant chewing and attention. He'll squeeze and chew the ball practically flat, and it has maintained its integrity and flash. He absolutely loves this ball. We'll likely buy another if/when it eventually deteriorates (since all things do over time!). Highly recommend., I have 2 tough chewers- a 60lb Staffie & 90lb black lab. They both want to play with it all the time and have yet to even take a chuck out of it. Usually these things last a day and it's torn apart but we are already into week 3 and it is still a coveted special toy. The led light makes it super fun. Now I need one for each of them. Highly recommend!!, My boy absolutely loves it !! He normally bully’s his sister for balls and just hides them but he actually plays with this ball and they will chAse each other for it he loves the light up feature. great product so far so good! hasn’t broken yet and it’s been almost 3 weeks !, Ball was AMAZING for 2 days, my dog loved the lights!! But then it stopped working :/ customer service was awesome and sent me a replacement ball ASAP but just took the replacement out of the box and it doesn’t even Light up at all. Must be some kind of manufacturer defect with these, disappointing!, My dog chews up every toy ever. She has a ball obsession, This ball is amazing! It's her favorite! It's a little squishy but not enough that she will tear it up, just enough squish that she can bite on when playing. She LOVES the strobe light. Love to watch it light up the hallway at night. She will play with this ball for hours on end. 1000% recommend & worth the price., This ball is amazing! Trip loves loves it! It changes colors every time it hits the ground. The colors are very vibrant! Quite indestructible!, My Westie loved this ball, but after less than an hour of use the LED stopped working!, I am really surprised when I saw the size of this ball as I have two dogs who can destroy anything and I mean anything. We have had it for now over a week and it is still in the same shape with no missing parts. The only thing which they really loved was the light it does not last very long. I would say it lasted for about a week which really kept my dogs interests. They still play with it but not as much since the light went out.]

reviews: [Pictured is a size "small" next to a regular-sized Kong. The small size is similar to a puppy-sized Kong – which is perfect because that's what we bought it for originally. The pieces at the bottom were meant to make the toy more challenging, but since our pup had really big pieces of kibble, the food wouldn't really come out at all, and then Mars would get bored and give up. I'm guessing with the right size kibble this would be a good choice for some dogs!, I have a very smart GSP that has these wild bursts of energy. Because of my job I can't always take him on a walk or play fetch with him when he needs it - so I rely a lot on brain toys and games that keep him occupied. What I love about this Busy Buddy is that that the hole has these little stoppers in the bottom that can stop the food from coming right out. My sweet doggo loves figuring out the best way to spin and flip it get the most kibble out! The loss of one star is due to the strong rubber smell on the product when i received it. It made me a little nervous to give it to my dog right out of the Chewy Box., By far the best fill-up and treat dispensing toy I've tried. The design is adorable, but it's also very practical. It takes a good while to get the food out and the rubber is strong, but flexible. Has a slight scent and it's quite interesting how it repels water. My old Kong got moldy quite quickly, despite thorough cleaning, this feature of being water resistant seems like it could help., I bought 3 of these after watching a video on YouTube. My 4 Pekingese gave up quickly, couldn't get treats OUT. I tried many snacks that they usually love, but they still gave up. They try, but the treats end up being wasted. The smoking gun was when I stuffed a Vienna sausage in one, and they love Viennas, but could not get it all out, even with part of it already out. Maybe someone can advise if I am doing something wrong or to try something that has worked for them? Thanks, Donna in Monroe, North Carolina, I love this thing! My rottie and lab mix are both power chewers (a jumbo bully is gone in about 5-10 minutes max), and this toy, despite my furry bears' best efforts, is still very much in one piece. No teeth marks, broken pieces, NOT A SCRATCH. Totally worth every penny!, The hole is smaller compared to the red kong version so it’s harder to get the treats out and i prefer that since it keeps my dog busier longer. It also has like some sort of ribbing on the inside to increase the difficulty. Will definitely buy again once toy is destroyed. It’s still intact a year later tho! And i have a heeler lol, We bought this a couple of years ago (at least) and our Dutch Shepherd/Heeler mix LOVES her purple squirrel. She is active and methodical with her play and means to get treats out of this. She will repeatedly pick up and drop/throw this thing to the ground hoping that as it bounces the pieces of treats will fall out. Our bigger dog (about 55lbs) has occasionally stolen it from her and it has serviced him chewing on it for a decent amount of time as well. Would recommend to anyone with a strong chewer or an active dog who needs a toy to keep them busy for a bit., This is the cutest lil guy to get a fun game of find the treats with my 14 weeks old golden. reviews: [This bone didn't last my dog 5 minutes before she started ripping pieces off. I knew it wasn't hard nylon but thought it would hold up better. As with everything you give your dog to chew they must be monitored, and if pieces are being chewed off the bone must be taken away., I would not recommend it for large breed puppies. Chewed it up and ate some of it., FlexiChew bone crumbled after only a few minutes of my dog chewing on it. Waste of money for large breeds., Scully will only chew this type of Nylabone. key_benefits: ['Designed to encourage positive play and teach your puppy healthy chewing habits from an early age while discouraging destructive chewing.', 'Erratic bouncy toy will keep your pal engaged and having fun while promoting healthy exercise.', 'Made with layered textures and built for long-lasting engagement to keep your furry pal happy, busy and entertained for hours.', 'Nubs help to clean teeth and reduce plaque and tartar while promoting healthy teeth and gums.', 'The rubber toy is a great way to have more interactive fun with your pal—just flick it and let your furry best friend try and catch it.']
reviews: [I bought one of these a year ago when we got our puppy and she has played with it every single day since. Somehow it got lost in our yard which is the only reason I had to buy another one. It was still in perfect shape in spite of us throwing it for her probably thousands of times, and her pouncing on it, chewing it, and prancing around with it. It is by far her favorite toy - she never gets tired of chasing it. It bounces, squeaks and rolls, and when it bounces or rolls, you never know which direction it is going which is what I think makes it so interesting to her. I wish Kong made more toys. They are the only things durable enough for this dog!, my dog is not only in love with this toy but she is obsessed with it, in particular this square one, she has so many other toys but only ever wants this one! I just bought her two more exactly like it, I have had my 50 pound, female pittie for about 2.5 years now and this was one of the first toys I ever bought her and it has continued to be her favorite. I have had to replace it about 3 times over the years, so it definitely isn't indestructible, but I don't think it's advertised as a "super" chewer anyway. We play fetch with it every day and every time she brings it back to me we play a little tug of War, so it takes its fair share of abuse and stands up well. It's really bouncy which makes it fun for her to chase and jump up in the air to catch. I also like that the rubber material is easy to clean. It gets dirty in the yard and all I have to do is rinse it off for her to play with it safely, I purchased because of Kong reputation for recently adopted a 10 month old 49lb puppy who is a chewer. The pup was able to get one of the knobs off before the end of the day. I really should have got the Kong Extreme instead. Don’t waste your money on this purchase like I did., I bought this hoping that the kong name would live up to its reputation, however, I was very disappointed when my 34 pound dog got a piece off within not even ten minutes of play. I thought this would be a good durable squeaky toy for my pup but he was sad when I had to take it away so quickly and fish the piece out of his mouth before he could swallow it., My dog is an "aggressive" chewer who likes hard chew toys. Sadly, she was banned from them due to her age and the impact on her teeth so now we've had to find alternatives to hard bones. This is a very sturdy toy BUT it has two layers, an outer layer, and an inner layer. She pulled the outer layer off in about 10 minutes and tried to eat it. She is now left with an inner layer that is firm but squishy, like a hard air-filled ball, and she has not been able to destroy it even though she tries to chew off the nubbins. I have to say, Kong for the win. We got the yellow and turquoise square-shaped one for large dogs., My 6 month old puppy chewed the pink balls off within minutes. Cute toy. Doesn't hold up., Cute toy but not recommended for big chewers. My German Shepherd had the nubs all chewed off within15 minutes:(, This item is the best. Keeps my English Bulldog busy for hours. And she has not been able to destroy it! LOVE Chewy, My 9lb Maltese tore into this toy in less than two weeks, ripping off some of the black nubs and tearing up the red plastic. He is a pretty vigorous chewer but I thought since this was a Kong it would last, but I guess not.]

reviews: [We've had two of these over 5 years, so I'd say they are long lasting. Our Bernese Mountain Dog is a strong chewer and we struggle to find toys and treats for him that will last. Loved this toy at first it was perfect for my teething Goldendoodle. reviews: [My puppy likes these toys, especially the blue rubbery one, but after a week of chewing the ribbons have broken off and she ingested a couple before I could get it away from her. The strings came out of the toy on top, the toy in the middle busted and stuffing came out, and the yellow piece on the bottom toy came off. Not happy with them. I do recommend for small puppies because the toys are small. So glad she’s not chewing on me!!!Thanks Chewy!!!, My 3 month old Yorkie/Chihuahua puppies DESTROYED these toys in less than a week. Another concern is they were able to remove the yellow ring from one of the toys and lastly, split open the soft toy, exposing the stuffing. I DO NOT recommend this product., we order EVERYTHING from CHEWY.we are DIEHARD CHEWY customers but these toys suck.they fell apart in no time and my dog is a chi mix so really not an aggresive chewer or dog..very dissapointed CHEWY, I have a little chihuahua and these are a perfect size and weight for her to carry in her mouth! She loves them, I've bought other Petstages toys for our pups and liked them. This one? Not so much. REALLY tiny, actually undersized for our 3 month old Havanese puppy who weighs about 4 1/2 pounds. The yellow ring on the rope toy was broken and discarded in no time, and the middle toy in this picture is so small I can't imagine a pup it would suit. The top "pinecone" toy is ok. So... one useful toy out of three for $9 is what we're left with. Not worth it., My 6 lb Yorkie liked the toys but destroyed each one in less than 1 week. No durable enough. The knots on the rope came undone and I had to throw the ring away because I worried she would choke on it. She pulled the strings from the bumpy blue one straight out. She has a few other toys, even plushies and these are the only ones she's destroyed., Puppies love these! These will keep your pup busy for hours. I gave this to my puppy every time he tried to bite on me since he is teething and it worked like a charm., This variety pack is the perfect pack to figure out what kind of teethers your puppy will like. We got this for our 3 month old 6 lb puppy & he enjoys all 3. These are great for toy or small dogs with tiny mouths. We freeze the plush fabric toy, & it’s held up well against sharky puppy teeth punctures. Both the pliable rubbery toy and rope toy are also intact although I wouldn’t recommend these for a heavy tugger, the yellow ring on the rope can easily slide off, as can the fabric knot inside the blue rubbery toy. I’ve used Petstages toys for my previous dog 12 years ago, & the brand continues to make quality products. Would love it if Chewy carried even more of their toys.]

reviews: [My 17 week old puppy loves this bone so much! I think it’s the combination of the hard bone and the rope but he just can’t stop chewing it. He’ll go walk around the room trying to find it and then happily settle down and chew for a while. Such a good buy!!, I am the owner of a six year old Boxer/Lab mix and a 4 month old German Shepherd Australian Shepherd mix. They are both heavy chewers! This toy has stood up to their ferocious gnawing. You can also put treats in it. My dogs love it. I would highly recommend this toy!, This is still holding up with our aggressive chewers! However they chew awhile and move on. It doesn’t hold their interest long. I am happy it’s still in one piece., These bones are great for dogs who aren't heavy chewers. Occasionally, they can bite through the bone and pieces need to be cut off, otherwise, they can swallow the pieces and case harm. They are a good size for dogs that are around 20 lbs to 25 lbs, and are about 4 1/2 inches in length. I learned early that all the cloth ties MUST be removed for safety. Dogs can get them off and swallow those as well, causing stomach and intestinal problems. (Surgery costs) Otherwise, the bone itself is fine for dogs...just watch your dogs and inspect the bones regularly., I know that my dog will chew on things, but she wouldn't touch this bone. I also offered it to my sister's dog, and she wouldn't touch it either. Maybe they are just fussy!, My 13 lb terrier tore off a one-inch piece in ten minutes. Not durable in the least. Also packaging says this chew should be fitted with treats, but no treats fit. The FAQ section of the Chewy page says it's not engineered to take treats -- which contradicts the packaging. Get it together Petstages!, This toy is well made. My dogs who love to chew up their toys within minutes haven't destroyed this one yet, and it's been two months. I definitely recommend!, Everytime FedEx comes with the box from chewy I have a huge female saints her name is Miss Chloe Willow and she will lay next to the box with one paw on it and her head and will not let anyone get by or near the Box and this toy is loved so much by my other Saint Bernard Sir Winston that he will put all four in his mouth and go lay in the corner and hoard them all he just loves them to pieces., Our hard chewer (2 year old Vizsla) not only loves this toy but still has one she’s had for over a year! We also believe it helps keep her teeth clean and gums healthy. Don’t hesitate to buy!!!, I am a big fan of petstages toys anyway, but this one is even more impressive. My pitty loves it. And she chews. Hard. Nonstop. She has had it for a week or so and there isn’t a single piece missing. Not even chew marks! I doubt it will last forever, but we’ll worth it.]
