reviews: [This is my second purchase of this toy - I actually lost his first one in a move and couldn’t find a replacement in the store, was happy to find it here on Chewy. I use Charlee Bear crunchy treats in the holes, they fit perfectly. My dog, a small dachshund, loves loves loves this toy. With a Charlee Bear treat in each hole, he has to bite down and break the treat to get it out of the hole. It’s a great way to occupy him a little bit and more fun for him than if I just gave him the treats. It can be extremely difficult to find treat toys for small dogs, so I was thrilled to find this one. I’ve not had any trouble with him damaging it or chewing it up. Once he’s done getting all the treats out , My PuPpEr got her first one a few months ago . I use it when i leave for work fill it with treats and freeze it to eliminate anxiety Nd it works well. But does get fatigued from use. However I do recommend it . I have ordered another at my pups 6 month mark will see how long this one lasts until. Can find something similar design that lasts longer , I stuff it with her cookie treats and peanut butter and freeze them and it occupies her time nicely she Calms down .. and chills out, All 3 of my dogs loved these.. Stuck canned dog food in it and froze it.. They worked at it for over a half hour having fun. So many different things that you can use to put in them and freeze, canned food, dehydrated food, yogurt, cottage cheese, PB. I also cut baby carrots and stuck them in there as well... Easy to clean, just have a bowl of hot water with dawn dish soap and let them soak in that for a few days, then rinse.., I bought one of these for Daisy when she was a pup (she’s 4 now) and replaced it about 6 months ago with a new one after the old one had been “loved” too much. Every morning I fill it with 4 small Bits treats, at least 4 baby carrots and sugar snap peas in season. Then the carrots get a dollop of Kong StuffN peanut butter squeeze treat. Daisy LOVES it and now Little Bear (12 weeks) does too (he has his own)! I can squeeze peanut butter in the crevices too, for another way to treat/occupy. I highly recommend. As I mentioned, Daisy’s first one lasted over 3 years before I could see teeth marks., My standard goldendoodle puppy has a lot of anxiety being left in his crate. I tried traditional frozen kongs, blankets, a snuggle puppy... nothing seemed to work! This kong filled with treats totally distracts him while I leave and gets him excited for his crate, since this is a crate only treat!, This did not live in our house a day it was destroyed in less than 8 hours. My dogs are chewers but I didn’t think that hard of chewers a little disappointed in this Kong product others we have purchased are great and still going strong., Very sorry I bought this KONG !! In less then 5 minutes my dog chewed right thru it. Because I didn't read carefully I didn't realize this was not a hard rubber toy., My dogs ate it with in 2 days! And they're just puppies! For $22 you would think it would last longer! Not very strong material!, I love kong toys because they're usually the only thing my dog cant destroy. Had this out of the box and it took less than 20 minutes for my 1 year old black lab to start ripping chunks off of it. Total waste of 20 bucks., I got this toy as a gift for my sister's dog! She is a chewer and this DOES NOT disappoint! She loves it and it's tuff so she can chew and chew! This is a great toy!]

reviews: [My 3lb Yorkie loves this bone. It’s one of his favorites. reviews: ["ATTENTION ANTLER LOVERS" My Pittie Enzo chews through EVERYTHING. We bought this because it seemed to be made of some pretty rugged plastic. It kind of wasnt a big hit until we stuffed an antler in the bottom (or top). My Enzo used his paws like hands and manages to hold everything like a person. Antlers are about the only thing that lasts around here but he has a hard time holding onto them. This this has kept him busy & happy forever! I have actually bought backups just incase they stop making it..., If your dog is a heavy chewer, they will chew this into pieces quickly. Once my dog got the treat out, she started chewing pieces of it off. It is not regular Kong material, it’s softer. A little disappointed. I was hoping for a toy that would keep her busy and also not shred., My dog loves this toy. It is just difficult enough to challenge her when she gets bored but she is able to get all the treats out by herself (I use the Nutro Crunchy triangular shaped treats). She has learned to either bounce the toy or squeeze it with her teeth with it turned in just the right direction so one of the treats fall out. Just perfect to keep her entertained but not frustrated., I ordered two of these. The blue one is soft enough that my little dog can bite it and open up the holes enough for kibbles to come out. The pink one is extremely tough. So tough that my Border Collie x Golden Retriever can't bite down on it enough, and it took me a hard time to squeeze kibbles in, but it hurt. I cut the pink one up a bit so they come out easier, but it was not easy to slide the edge of the scissors in there. The pink one can rough up a finger and my BC x GR is a licker usually when trying to get treats/kibbles out of toys like this, so no doubt she hurt her tongue trying to fit it though. ~*~ I haven't bought more than these two, so can't say for sure if all pink ones , My 6 month old 5 pound puppy looooooves this toy. I fill it with her favorite treats and she plays hours.she chews and tosses it all over the place. She comes and goes to and from the toy. Whenever she sees it after leaving it she pounces. It’s pure entertainment for me as well. I love Kong!, Kong toys are the best. My Labradoodle is crazy about her wobbler and several other treat toys from the brand. Sadly this item doesn't make the strength cut. Tally chewed into it within an hour of arrival., My dog is not an aggressive chewer. She enjoys the treat enticement, and the long neck to chew on. It holds up very well to her play., We have the Mike toy that goes along with this one. It's held up GREAT, so we wanted to add this one for a little challenge. Well, as many of the other reviews suggest (as well as the description from Kong, to be fair) this is NOT a good addition if you have an aggressive chewer, as it WILL get destroyed within minutes., My dog chewed off small pieces of this toy the first time we used it while she attempted to get the treat out. Luckily I was watching and took the toy away before she swallowed a small piece of rubber, but was very disappointed that we got no use out of this. Fun idea, bad execution., My dog loves this toy, and spends hours at a time getting the dog treats out that I put inside. I also stuff cheese in the top part that looks like a vase, and she occupies herself by getting the cheese out. This has been her favorite toy now for years. KONG company, please don't stop making these!]

reviews: [My pup is an extreme chewer. I bought a lot of different toys to redirect him from chewing on my furniture and walls. He chews and doesn't tear, though, so I don't know how it would hold up in that scenario., This is our fourth of this line of rubber Duralast chew toys. They withstand our Great Dane chewing on them daily. The only reason we had to order more is because he snuck them outside and buried them., My furry friend hated these bones - and so did I. First, the foul smell is a real turn off for humans and pets! Second, the RubberChew is no way near as durable as Nylabone's DuraChew. I guess I should just stick with what I know me and my pooch like!, I have a 2 year old mix large dog (GSP and catahoula) he chewed through this rubber bone within minutes. Pieces of rubber were everywhere. Not recommended for younger chewing dogs. We also have a 10 year old lab who did great with it., This didn’t even last 5 mins with our one year old Rottweiler. She had it in pieces before I turned around. Completely different material than our other Nylabones., Jake really likes his nylabone chew toy. It keeps him busy for quite some time when he's chewing on it. Glad I bought it for him., Gave my huskies these Christmas eve. They looked like they loved them that night. Its been a week and they haven't touched them. Not even when I try and tug a war. My dogs are obsessed with nylabones we're shocked that all 3 huskies show no interested., It's not actually bone and their are little bumps all over it. And it does it look like a bone and it does it have hardly any small or flavor to it. Both of my boys don't like it, Unfortunately for my two boys (35lb husky mix, 55lb pit mix) these bones did not hold up more then a hour or so. I have big time chewers, and not much lasts in my household. I would recommend these for dogs who are not extreme chewers because they loved them while they lasted., my small dog did not like this at all maybe because it's rubber. Seems to prefer something she can chew.]

reviews: [I really thought that this would be able to withstand my 30 lb pup for at least a week. Nope, The squeaker was gnawed out and a gaping hole was left after just 5 minutes with my precision chewer. I had high hopes, but this just isn't the toy for my girl., The large is a very large toy. It’s More for mastiff or Burmese mtn dog. My 80 lb pit likes it but it’s just big enough he doesn’t bother too much with it. I wish I got the medium. Sometimes it’s hard to tell if he needs med or large. No big issue., Our Boxador loves fetch, and this is a great toy for outdoor fetch. We got the large one, and she loves to run around with it in her mouth until we tussle it away for the next fetch. The squeaker requires a good amount of pressure, and it is well engineered into the structure so that it can not be easily chewed out, which is great for her., I have 2 60lb lab mixes that are true power chewers. These were on sale so I figured I wasn't out much when they rip through them in minutes. Honestly, I'm shocked. Its been about 2 weeks and these things are still going strong! I may have just jinxed it but I am pleasantly surprised so far! They are also far bigger than I expected them to be., My dog, Beau, carries this bone everywhere. It’s almost like a pacifier to him. It’s a great training tool also because I throw it out in the back yard and he grabs it and does his business and then comes back. Easy peasy!, I have a 3 month old, 19 lb puppy, so maybe that’s the issue, but it seems that even myself, as an adult, I need to use excessive force to actually get the toy to squeak. The material and durability is great, just wish it was an easier squeak., My beagle loves squeaky things but you have to push really hard to make it squeak. Doesn’t chew on it. Gives no attention to it., I have smaller dogs, so I can't say anything about sturdiness for a large breed. My dogs really like this toy, and I get the sense that it will last a long time. If the squeak matters to you, I can only get a very tiny squeak out of it...and that is if I squeeze it extremely hard. My dogs cannot make it squeak, and that is ABSOLUTELY fine with me!! They have plenty of toys, that make plenty of noise! I have been very happy with their other toys, of the same brand., My dog had it torn up in one day! Would not recommend this toy to a heavy chewer dog!, My pup loves this toy! She runs through the house squeaking it as she carries it around. It’s thicker than I thought it would be so she’ll have it for a while. I don’t think this would stand up to an aggressive chewer though.]

reviews: [My pit mix and I ABSOLUTELY LOVE this toy. Hands down. Purchase it for the love of God. Not only does my (70 lb) boy pick it up for frequent playing, but it has given me absolute peace of mind with regard to his eating habits. Prior to being diagnosed with pancreatitis, my boy would get an occasional bout of moodiness and refuse to eat, even GUARD his food; I mean: hackles and snapping, due to his pain, the baby. Now if we're traveling or off schedule and I sense he's not inclined to eat - I just put his (dry) food in the toy - and he does not mind me being in the same room!! Crisis averted. Hospital bills averted! Love love love!! This is my second purchase, NOT because the one of three years, I bought this toy for my 78 pound boxer/pitbull mix 2 years ago and it is still going strong!! She is tough on her toys and can easily ruin “indestructible” toys in no time. This one is still looking brand new after 2 years of almost daily play! There’s 3 separate treat compartments and the unusual shape of the toy makes it bounce all over the place in an unpredictable way., I had a smaller one for my lab/pit mix and decided to upgrade. She loves this one more than the last and is always bringing it to me to be refilled. I prefer the larger one as it allows for more variations in treat sizes. It's the perfect size for a medium-size dog. Enjoy pups- From Dawn the dog! Yes, dogs can type!, The rugger smell of this is HORRID. I tried handwashing it and running it through the dishwasher, but all it did was make the other dishes in my dishwasher smell like the rubber. Had to rewash other dishes, this is either returned or trashed., The 'New' polyethylene odor has stopped me from giving to my dog. I bought 3 similar dog treat toys at the same time. I have had one of these treat dispensers for years. What I don’t like is that it is heavily scented/perfumed. It smells like vanilla and is so strong that my entire living room smells like it. I washed it with warm soapy water and it continues to give off a strong odor. While the odor isn’t unpleasant, it worries me that my pup is investing chemicals., My dog absolutely loves this toy. Has had it for a couple of days, and so far, it hasn't been destroyed. I bought the medium size and the small. Small works perfectly for my medium sized Basenji (30lbs). Finally, I found something that will last me awhile. If it does get destroyed (eventually), I'll buy another. It's hard to find toys that hold her attention for very long., I think this treat will be a bit better for my dog when the weather is warmer and I can make it a frozen treat for him. The prongs inside of it make it hard to know at all when a treat will come out (i have cut them shorter). The toy mainly needs to be bounced and thrown for a treat to come out which my dog isn't all that fond of (not much a fetch player) but I will try more with it when it's nicer out and we can use it outside. I'd recommend it more for dogs who are inclined to playing fetch like that but for those more fond of pushing a toy around or chewing/licking there are different toys more geared for that., Great design and challenging puzzle. reviews: [I didn't notice that these bones are for 'medium chewers'. I definitely have three extreme chewers. My 40-50 lb dogs had these bones chewed up into almond-sized pieces within about 20 minutes. By the time I realized it, I was scrambling to try and pick up all the pieces as they were attempting to ingest the chunks of bone. The major problem I have is the way the bone came apart into chunks., I didn't realize how small these were. Once my dog bit part of the bone off, we had to take it away due to fear of him choking. This is definitely for smaller dogs., My dogs loves these. He will find them and then go find them., Great way for your pup to release stress. My yorkie runs to find his to help with his anxiety., My puppy doesnt care for them but my big dog uses them, Be aware: "Product is not intended to be eaten or ingested. If you think your dog swallowed a piece, take the product away and contact your veterinarian." What the...? Our dogs have not been taught to spit; nor do I think I could train them to. That, plus the fact that my patience and interest does not include watching my dog masticate for long periods has eliminated Nylabone as a viable product to give my dogs. I will need to find something different to amuse my canines and relax. btw - Chewy has identified Nylabone as chew "toys." Some toy... Sorry to be so negative. But it is my fault. reviews: [I love this dog toy! Its very durable for our 78 lb husky mix aggressive chewer. Very few toys can stand up to her powerful chewing. We purchased the largest one. My dog would not put it down, i think he actually spent over 3/4 hours straight chewing on it the day we received it. It is so so so worth the money. The treat rings are tough to get off, and my pups LOVE the scent/taste of them as well. The best toy ever. I can’t recommend enough, This is the second Bristle Bone Dog Toy for our dog. He loves it. I use the rawhide discs with it as well as peanut butter or ‘spray cheese’....cheese in a can.. I am amazed at how much better his teeth look. He was able to get the end off and chewed the threads on the post. That made it a little difficult to screw it back together. He has used it so much that I noticed some missing chunks of bristles so I bought a replacement bristle bone toy., Our dogs love these! We get the raw hides that go with them and it keeps them busy!, No one in my house likes the very strong odor of this toy, including my two Goldens. Aside from that, it looks really sturdy and is dishwasher safe., My dog is a lab mix and I've tried all kinds of things to keep his teeth tartar-free and thought this would do the trick - brushing while he's having fun! reviews: [Maggie loves her new bones! The rule of thumb is if you can't bend it with your hands and make an indent with your fingernail on it, it's too hard. Both of theses chew toys are flexible and soft enough to be safe for teeth but not so soft that its a danger (at least not to my labs chewing power)., Took the puppy just over a month to reduce these to a one inch blue piece and hundreds of smidgens. I didn't love the aftermath., Joan my Guide Dog is not an aggressive chewer but finds great satisfaction with both of these "Chew" products. I ended up throwing it away because I was afraid she could get some little pieces off of it at that rate. It is not for heavy chewers., My dogs love these bones. We have them in many flavors. The sweet potato smells funny but they don't care. For a pittie mix, standard poodle, and basenji we buy the large and extra large., I am not sure if it's b/c my smaller dog is a tough chewer, but I had to take it away after a day or two, so she wouldn't swallow the pieces she chewed off..., Received this through Pup Box originally but ordered two more. Both my senior and my puppy love this bone. However, it is a plastic chew and after some heavy chewing you will have to take it away as the plastic degrades. That should be expected of any plastic toy though. I never used the little holes... Just didn't seem worth it to try and clean later., Hard to put any flavoring on bone. I tried peanut butter and it made more of a mess than what it was worth. My dog does like carrying it around and it isn’t heavy, My Australian Shepherd loves to chew and really loved to chew this toy. She chewed it so much that the ends started to get very pokey and I had to take it away from her to prevent any cuts in her mouth. I would not recommend this chew toy if your pup is a heavy chewer., Obviously if you had to choose between mint and bacon egg and cheese flavored bones I think everyone would go for the latter so my dog has really left it untouched but it’s a good size bone and hopefully he’ll start to play and chew it., I just pulled this item out of my chewy autoship box, and still sealed in the package with no tears or punctures, this chew had dirt on it inside the package. Not sure how this was ok’d through the manufacturing process but it makes me question the companies quality control in every manner., This is the perfect size for my 20 pound Boston Terrier. He loves it. Although I think he may like the chicken flavor a bit better as he still sneaks off with the large chicken one when he has the opportunity. Size doesn't seem to be a huge issue as he can still comfortably chew on the size large. It is very sturdy. Just like any toy you will still need to exam it in case sharp edges occur., Where is the mint? No smell at all. My shepard doesnt even touch it. Waste of money.]

reviews: [This lil senior pup wasn’t feeling well the last few days ... but you’d never know it once his Chewy order arrived ! I ordered this bone as one of his birthday presents- and while he doesn’t often chew or play with his toys , he took to this immediately! It seems durable and he likes the scent/flavor. When he dropped it behind his bed mattress , he expectantly stared at me until I found it for him ! This spoiled boy is definitely having a Happy Birthday!, My dog loved this and has not destroyed it yet! He does like the flavor which I wasn't sure about, but all good so far!, Elliott loves these flavored bones. I occasionally spread peanut butter on these bones as an extra treat. He's a chewer and they hold up fairly well. Pieces have never broken off like some other bones., I bought this for my puppy. It's perfect, since she can't choke on it., I ordered two so my two dogs could each have one. My husky hides them when she gets a chance., My pups and their friends can’t get enough of these bones., I was interested because it was a different flavor for a dog treat. It has a very pleasant aroma and i am pleased that it is made in the US. Brodie could hardly wait for me to get this out of the package and really seems to like it., My puppy loves this toy. She is constantly gnawing on it . It seems to soothe her as she is going through this teething phase., She was obsessed the minute I gave it to her! She loves it and noshed on it for hours! It is showing minimal chewing damage, there are many hours left for her to enjoy! Soft toys she rips apart so fast so this one is perfect!, Two month old puppy got this one. She loves it. Will chew this one, then get a soft toy, back to the hard again]

title: Starmark Crunching Barbell Treat Dispensing Tough Dog Toy
descriptions:
['The Crunching Barbell Treat Dog Toy provides a fun new chewing challenge for your dog. The barbell is large enough to hold an inserted treat rod plus interactive treats for plenty of playful options. Simply add the interactive treats into the treat rod, then place the filled treat rod into the barbell and watch your pup go wild as he tries to get to the center. The treat rod is designed to break as your dog chews the barbell, releasing small pieces and interactive treats as he continues to play. This sturdy toy is made from a virtually indestructible material that is stronger than rubber, free of latex, vinyl, and phthalates, and dishwasher safe.', 'Treats sold separately.', 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.', '

                        See all items by Starmark
']
key_benefits: ['Provides hours of challenging play and is perfect for pets with separation anxiety.', 'Holds one inserted treat rod and interactive treats. Stuff the treat rod with the interactive treats and as your pet chews on the barbell, the treat rod will break and release the treats.', "Virtually indestructible and stronger than rubber. It's free of latex, vinyl, and phthalates, so you can feel confident about letting your loved one play with this toy.", "Dishwasher safe and floats. You can bring to the pool, beach, or lake and get out some of your pup's excess energy.", 'Available in medium and large sizes so you can pick the appropriate one for whatever sized dog you have.']
reviews: [My bernedoodle is OBSESSED with this “toy.” When I tell him to go get a toy from his three huge baskets full of toys, it’s this one he grabs and brings to me. When I’m grading or otherwise engaged, he brings me this “toy” and puts it in my lap. If we are rough housing, he stops everything and decides he wants this “toy.” With or without treats, he loves this thing. (Yes, I know to fill it with treats because he is pretty much begging me to do it by dropping it on my lap, LoL, but even if I don’t, he is content to sniff and lick and chew at it without anything in it.) I’ve had to purchase several of these because my newfypoo tries to steal and hide it from him since he knows it will detract from, I have a super chewer that loves to figure out his interactive toys. He will figure out an easier way eventually but for now this new one had him busy all night!!!, My Australian shepherd is a tough chewer and this toy stands up to that well. The rod inside and more treats in the rod keeps her interested for hours., It lasted all of 5 mins my American Bulldog puppy had the end tore off. I don’t know where they get virtuously indestructible from, For the price .... this toy is just okay. Its rubber and I think the treat is kind of hard to get to. He is not as interested in this toy as I would have liked., This is a great interactive toy for my dog, Henry, who is a 20 lb. doxie. This toy is a challenge to him and he'll spend as much time as it takes to get the treat from the barbell. I don't use the treats that come with the Barbell because they're too hard for his tiny teeth so I stuff it with other healthy treats. I pack it TIGHT so it's not too easy. He jumps & flips around & squeals as soon as he knows the treat is coming up after his afternoon workout. It's very durable, only have to replace it after it gets too stretched out & treat is too readily removable. This size is probably meant for a larger dog but it works for my little fella because he takes on the challenge to "getter done.", A little big for our boxer pup but I'm sure she will grow into it. Has lots of options for stuffing - I pop "frosting" and kibble into every gap and freeze it - keeps our little girl engaged and happy!, I think this toy would be good for a more patient dog who likes chewing and puzzles. My dog gave it a few minutes before she chewed an end off and took the treats out. She is a powerful chewer and apparently doesn't have time to waste with puzzles when it comes to treats., This product feels softer than most heavy chewer toys so I was concerned initially. I put the stick in it and gave it to my 6 mos old GSD. HE IS AN EXTREME CHEWER. I fully expected it to be destroyed in minutes. Two days later and it’s still in perfect shape. I only took away one star because he was able to get the stick out quite quickly. It just means I will be buying more sticks but to find a toy that he doesn’t destroy is a miracle for us., I don't put the stick in because he pushes it in and gets bored trying to lick it out. Putting smaller treats in though, he figured out it comes out the end so he tilts his head and shakes it...]

reviews: [I got the petite size for my 6 month old Cavalier puppy. He has major health issues and has to be limited on play time so he spends quiet time in his play pen. This has kept him entertained. I think I would get the next size up for him though. Perfect size for my yorkies who are 4, 6 and 8 pounds!, My little 15# dog takes this bone with her to bed at night. If she forgets it, I hear her jump down and head out to look for it. She loves it. Good for her teeth too., I've got a lot of dogs and I foster dogs. I can tell you, these are the best bones. All my dogs love them and I've never had one break. One more though. My dogs (Chihuahua to German Shepard) only like the small size. IDK why, but they will not chew the medium or large size! Dogs are funny. I just wish they weren't so dang expensive., Our Bullmastiff loves this bone just wish it lasted a little longer. Can’t wait till you get them back in stock. Love it, My puppy took just a little while to warm up to it, then she really liked it which is why I gave it three stars, however it has only been a few weeks and I am already feeling the need to take it away because I am afraid that if she chews on it much more that a small piece might come off... I thought that this was made to be chewed on!, I buy the plastic chew bones because my Rotts are big chewers. They seem to like this one and as long as they are happy, so am I, My German Shepard mix lasted about 5 mins before pieces were breaking off. Sadly it was in the trash in short order. Bummer for both of us., My aggressive chewer started shredding tiny pieces off the first day. She’s usually not one to eat “inedible” bits of toys and usually just leaves a pile of destruction. However, given how small the shreds are, I’m sure she’s ingested some of this synthetic material, which is concerning. I would mind so much if it was edible. Plus, it looks like someone had a cheese grating party in my hallway. So, it’s going in the trash after 2 days., My dogs love these bones, but I was having trouble finding them. Then Chewy saved the day!, my little puppy loves this, i'm getting more of them for her, they are small enough for her small mouth]

reviews: [I was excited at first because it seems like a heavy duty product, but my 1 year old pit bull terrier destroyed this within 10 minutes. The smaller tapered section was easily ripped to destroy the squeaker and the overall product. NOT “tough” and definitely NOT “virtually indestructible”. Do they test these toys on chihuahuas?, It seemed like the sturdiest toy we have bought so far but the tapered end made it easy for my pit bull mastiff to destroy. Maybe a redesign would help - I think a round version would work better, This is seriously the best toy we’ve had. You can load it with treats and it’s indestructible!! Our Aussiedoodle chew, chew, chews on it to try to get treats out, and carries it around all over. He even carries it around when it's empty. It’s definitely his go to toy!! It seemed so simple, I almost didn't buy it. I'm so glad I did. We've had this toy for over a year and our super duper razor sharp teeth chewer of a dog has not gotten through this. You can load treats in easily and the squeaker rarely squeaks, which is nice. When it does squeak, its pretty quiet. I've reccomended this toy to so many friends with dogs, I decided I should also write a review. Best Toy Ever!!, 75 lb pit bull tore apart within ten minutes :( had a good scent compared to some of the harsh plastic smelling toys though. Just didn't last., This toy is the perfect combination for my dog: squeaky and full of treats to work on getting! After a week of playing, the toy is still intact! Usually squeaking toys are destroyed in minutes. This has 4 rubber fingers inside the the opening that make it more challenging to get the treats (the directions say you can trim those back if you like, but when you do, there is no going back.) Also the squeaker is still squeaking. It's not like a regular squeaky toy where she can pull out the squeaker and destroy it. Definitely will order another if the time comes!, Dogs went crazy when given new chew toys. Sadly they’ve been taken away. Toys are made in China. I do not trust toys made in China for my pets. Very disappointing. Hopefully I can exchange them., Both my dogs loved this one- and I didn’t even put any treats in it! My 5-month old seemed to love just carrying it around hanging on to it by the small end. And my older dog used the large end and squeaked it! He loves squeak toys, I may order another so they can each have their own., So it is a good concept. I ordered a medium and a large, one for each dog and the smaller medium I made the mistake of not chopping the treats in half so now the toy is full stuffed of treats that the poor little dog can’t get out and he’s getting very ticked. I tried cutting the prongs and thumping it and squeezing and I can’t even get them out. My mistake. The large size is difficult but after thumping they eventually come out. Had I chopped the treats into smaller pcs it could have been a fun toy. I’ll have to pitch the smaller one if he ever gets away from it. My bad. So just make sure not to put too large of treats in it., I trimmed the prongs like it stated to for easier access to the treats, but my pup still just doesn’t like the toy itself. It doesn’t have a lot of treat capacity and he doesn’t like to play with it. He has 3 treat dispensing toys and this is the only one he doesn’t like., Our ten month old Border Collie is now being called Destructo Pup. All the soft toys with squeakers are put away. Some should be thrown away, some repaired, some await until Katie has no more teeth. She wants the squeakers out and she wants them out now! This toy has a squeaker, is fun and has not been injured at all by her demands. Highly recommend.]

reviews: [I ordered five different highly durable toys from Chewy at the same time for a 55 lb shepherd cross that is a moderate plus chewer. He was able to rip this toy apart in about five minutes from when he first received it. There is a hole in each of the three ends into which treats can be placed. Even though there were no treats in the toy, he was able to quickly rip a piece of it off starting at the opening. In addition to the piece that he ripped out, he was also able to start to rip the toy apart in the same area (With time, he would of been able to remove additional pieces of it). All of the other four toys that I purchased are still intact; including a similar toy made by the same company, Wow! We have two super tough chewers in our home- a 110# rottie/lab mix and a 70# shepherd/pyr puppy. We have struggled to find a toy that lasts even 5 minutes in our home. Nothing seems to work until we got this one!! It took about 6 months before they started to pull off rubber chunks. The 3-pronged bone is the only one that has lasted that long, some of the other toys from this brand were torn up within a day or two but this one lasted for a looooong time :) Tough rubber but soft too so the dogs are actually interested in it unlike kong toys. Hollow inside so you can add treats or peanut butter! Definitely recommend!!!!, My German Shepherd destroys most toys within the first hour. She loves this toy! It is kinda heavy. I fill it with peanut butter and she will lick on it and stick her immensely long tongue all the way to the bottom to get the last drop. I swear it's like she's sucking on a pacifier when she gets to the bottom. It's hilarious., I just received the two of the toys today, and the puppy has been chewing on it for approximately 45 minutes and has already chewed a chunk off. Might be ok for light to moderate chewers, she definitely liked it but it didn't last., I dont recommend it for Strong chewers. My lab has chewed off pieces of it., My dog is a 47 pound mix who is a super chewer. This toy is such a tough rubber that it looks almost new after months of play. It is quite heavy but that doesn’t bother me or my dog any. The holes in each end are a decent size to hold a bunch of apple chunks or treats and acts as an interactive toy for my pup to try to get them out. An overall great buy!, I would compare this to a KONG and I use in similar fashion by smearing a bit of peanut butter in one or all of the opening as a treat., Took my dog about 20 minutes to be pulling big red rubber chunks off of the ends of this toy. So, while it may be okay for less strong chewers - it didn't stand up well to my strong chewer., My Active Frenchie LOVES it. It’s durable and easy to clean, Our dog loved the toy when it came out of the package, and immediately proceeded to chip the tough plastic and break off pieces. reviews: [We have a 1 year old St. Bernard puppy and he has not destroyed this chew toy yet although we've had it for almost 6 months. We also like the bright color, which makes it easy to find when he takes it outside in the yard. We would definitely buy it again., We have a 50 lb collie mix who destroys most toys in minutes. Unfortunately one of the toddlers let him have it back and he's spent the last few weeks destroying it and ripping it into smaller pieces. Apparently I didn't pick up some fast enough and found them the other day after some rain in a pile in the yard. If you have a tough chewer I wouldn't get this toy, it won't last long., I bought this at a local retailer. I didn’t realize Chewy sold it. I’m so happy that they do. This toy is GREAT!! But it would be nice if the depth of the toy was longer so I could stuff more treats in it., My dog Riddick really loves this treat-toy! I will never buy anything from this company again., My boy who destroys everything plays with this and has not been able to make a dent in it. He carries it around, plays tug and chews on it. reviews: [My pug, Pippa, has had all kinds of chew toys and toys available since she was a puppy, but I kept catching her chewing on cabinets and such even long after losing her puppy teeth (and having the stuck stragglers removed during her spay surgery). These were purchased for a puppy class as prizes and as chews for personal dogs. The material sheets off with minimal Pressure - even from a senior dog with poor teeth. Though taken away quickly Once we realized how they ToT chunked and peeled apart, vomiting recurred in both dogs who ingested small amounts here, and all but one pup who had received as a prize did as well. Be very cautious of pups being able to ingest shreds and pieces of this toy. We have never had similar reactions from Nylabone or, This is the first time I have been disappointed by a chew toy like this. My boys (Cane Corso and Anatolian Shepherd) are very heavy chewers but toys like this usually can last them a while. Not this one! They had it destroyed in less than 24 hours! Will not be buying again., For my 4 month old puppy this is great but my 4 year old dog he started to destroy it in seconds. It has a great shape that lets them hold it and they really do enjoy it but it is not good for dogs that like to chew., I bought several of these bones for my dogs because they were on sale. reviews: [My 65 lb Belgian shepherd approaches toys the way a velociraptor would, but we have had so much luck with the Orka tire toy I thought I'd give this a try. I knew he'd tear the rope out immediately - and he did - but it's easy to thread a new rope toy through for a floss and a few more hours of play. The toy itself is thin and flimsy, so I wouldn't give it a super chewer 'unstuffed.' Then I pushed my luck and stuffed the blue part with treats. This marked the end of the blue toy. RIP blue toy, I use two of these for agility. Equal toys to help with start lines., My 15 month old lab loves this toy. Normally she tears into toys. This one she's playing with. Throwing it around. Laying on her back and chewing it. It's great for fetch., Again, my Jade had this in exactly 3 separate pieces in 30 minutes or less. Very cute, but a HUGE waste of money for my growing puppy., Well another good selection. This holds up to my Frenchies., My puppy just loves this toy it’s one of his favorites, My dog loves this! Hard for him to destroy too. It is perfect for my high energy pup., Our puppy loved this toy for the entire 10 min it lasted. the plastic is more of a soft rubber that was very easily destroyed. We had to keep watch and take away the chunks of rubber/plastic that she tore off the toy with ease. May be good for a dog with no teeth...lol, We have a eight week old toy poodle it’s hard to find toys she will chew on due to her size. As soon as I pulled this one out of the box she packed it off and has not put it down. Thank you for a great toy., My 10 month old black mouth cur had little blue pieces of rubber everywhere. I did not expect it to last forever but thought it would make it past the 15 minute mark.]

reviews: [Bought two of these for my dogs for Christmas, and they were the worst! reviews: [I have a working dog, - one year old German Shepherd. She LOVES this toy, but while it is durable, it has a tendency get stuck on her teeth. For other dogs this may cause a panic. Usually my dog takes a few seconds to paw it off, or I have to go over and pry it off of her canine., My dog loved it but it only lasted about 5 minutes before he chewed the first piece off!!!, My hyper anxious German Shepherd is not interested at all in this ball. It’s real hard and too big of bumps. The picture shown here of the “hyper chewz ball” is NOT what the 2 I received look like? The 2 balls I received have 6 large hard bumps., It is very sturdy. My daughters dog likes it. This is the second one that we bought. My grandson wanted one for his dog. We had a hard time trying to find it and we found it on your website., Switched from another ball that was hard to chew but weighed too much- we use a tennis racket and other ball would give a concussion. This ball is light and our power chewer hasn’t destroyed it yet-3 months. Bought another for travel toy., My puppy is beyond hyper and she’s a biter. She’s only 7 mths so I tried this and it is unbelievable. Saving us some puncture wounds on our hands, I hate this toy. It has lasted for well over a year and the dog is still so obsessed with it. It is still in great condition. But he is soooo annoying with it., My German Shepard loves the toy and doesn’t destroy it like he does others, My two are not power chewers at all and have not been allowed to sit and chew on this. It’s been an interactive only toy ... they’ve only had some fetch sessions ... and it has extremely deep indentions . They have other balls by chuck-it and kong that far surpass this ball. I just now threw it away as there were so many holes I was concerned pieces would start flaking off . This is just from playing fetch and squishing it in their mouths as they are retrieving it . Won’t be buying again., We have a Belgian malinois, and these balls last the longest. He is a very strong chewer. He plays catch for hours. Fantastic product!]

reviews: [I’m not sure how this product has so many great ratings. We have an 8 lb Jack Russell/yorkie mix and a 12 lb. cavalier/yorkie mix that are both big chewers. reviews: [Squeaker lasted about 4 hours. The toy itself is already splitting on the edges where the treats would go. I give it another 48 hours with our Amstaff before it gets binned., My Bully dog still plays with this toy from 9 months ago. It still squeaks and is only partially destroyed., Our 1 year old dachshund/corgi absolutely loves this toy. Not so much as treat toy. But as a fetch or tug of war toy this is his favorite. It does however have a strong Oder. I kept this outside on the deck for a few days and that helped. This is the second one I have ordered. The first one is holding up well to vigorous playing. Reason for buying a second one, what if something happened to his favorite toy!, This is her second one but only because we lost her first one at some point during a cross country move. She loves to play fetch with it and it has held up really well to her chewing. Better then some kong toys. I stuff it with treats for her when we are going to be gone for a longer time and have to crate her. The squeak is the first thing to die but even that last way longer on this toy then others she has had., My 2 yr old Australian cattle dog destroyed it in 2 days, I made the mistake of buying a medium and large for my 2 dogs. My husky tried to squeak the medium one and gave up. Now she won't even try to get the treats. My pit lab mix loves the treats but can't get them to squeak! Mind you, this dog destroys every toy with his strong jaws!! My son, who works out, has to use both hands., My pittie loves to destroy any toy he comes across and this has/still surviving!, Two arms of this toy hold large kibble that is loosley held by little match-sized fingers. The third is solid and makes the toy heavy enough to throw far outdoors. The design makes it pop up and bounce and roll. The center has a squeaker that is hard for my 4-month old Vizsla puppy to sound off, but the one-year-old Siberian Husky is able to. I just press it to get them excited to fetch it. Toys (and dogs) are best used interactively, so even though it is very durable this toy shouldn't be left with a heavy chewer to destroy., My dog has over a half dozen busy buddy toys that keep him engaged all day. He hasn’t annoyed us with the one end that squeaks., This product wasnt put in with the other items that I originally ordered and I called chewy and told them. reviews: [Our 2 year old lab, is very happy with this toy and it keeps him busy at least 15 minutes. The only issue is that the ball is huge and it really doesn’t bounce, he can’t open his mouth wide Enough to hold por chew the ball, By likes the ends and treats,, One of my dogs favorite toys he’s ever gotten. Great size, incredibly durable, and he loves the treat rings. Granted he got them off within around 30 minutes (but he’s a 75lb Pitt mix, so is expected) and he doesn’t love it without the treat rings, but put on another treat ring and it’s like a brand new toy again!! Highly recommend!!!!, My pup has no interest in it, even with the treat on it., Gizmo and I love these for fun and treats. This time I picked wrong size ( too big). We have already replaced the toy for each of them because they have worn it out , however they still use the ball part of the old toy . Love this !!!!, This is a great toy for a chewer but once the treats are gone they might lose interest., PetSafe has few of these type of toys where you need to buy these chewy rings and that keeps your dog busy for a while. This specific one isn't the best. It doesn't really bounce therefore if you buy one type it's enough, do not get this one though! Chewy is just wonderful as always when I have a problem with a product so I don't hesitate calling and share my concerns., They loves the treats and just loves to chew on the bone part of the toy! I'm buying another 2 so they don't have wait for one to finish etc., I ordered a large bouncy bone which was a bit too big, but she ate the couple rings that came with it. So I ordered more rings but medium rings by mistake. So- I ordered a medium bouncy bone, and she wouldn't eat the rings that came on it or the replacement large and small rings I ordered for both sized toys. The original large rings were darker brown, all the others are a lighter gray tinted color. There's a problem with them. Whether it's manufacturing or storage conditions I don't know. I advised Chewy.com that a problem existed, and perhaps the warehouse storage conditions or manufacturer's lot number should be checked. I indicated I didn't want more unusable rings. Chewy.com replaced , Bought 3 of these so each pup would have their own. Entertained them of HOURS!]

reviews: [Our black mouth cur, found this to be all most as challenging as the flying saucer. We able to fill with jerky or biscuits treats. And easy to find and pick up when empty. Plus, since it’s 100% non-toxic and BPA-free, you can feel good about bringing it out to play every day.', 'Created especially for paw-some games of fetch and not designed to be a chew toy. reviews: [AS DOGS, WE LOVE OUR NEW BARBELL - TOUGH TO CHEW ON, BUT CAN'T TEAR IT UP!!, My year old Labrador Retriever chewed this toy to pieces; and we didn't have it for very long. I’ve bought a few other nerf dog toys that haven’t been very durable so I didn’t have high hopes for this one but my dogs have had this for months without destroying it !!, Thought it would be good for my powerful chewer, but it only lasted 3 days. I was getting harder toys, but he suffered a trauma in a canine and dentist only recommends rubber toys., Rugged toy and has held up to our Lemon Pointer pup! Would definitely buy again!, I have 3 90-120 pound dogs and these things will last forever unlike most toys that get destroyed within a few hours of giving them to them., Thought this would be good for my aggressive English bulldog chewers, but he got it for 10 minutes and good off the sides and had to take it away from him., This toy wears our two year old Pitt Bull OUT.... We spent ALOT of money on toys. He would destroy them in minutes. Nerf Barbell stands up to the time. TUFF, DURABLE and Pitt Bull proof. Finally a happy Pit Bull Mommy, Thank You Nerf., This was a lot better than the last toy, lasted a lot longer but for a Pit Bull it has to be tuffer., We have 2 lab pups and they had the center tore out in no time, but the balls on the end are still holding up.]

reviews: [My small dog chewed the top off in a couple of hours. Had to throw it away!, Got 2 of these because it was a Chewy deal. Designed to satisfy strong chewers, this toy includes durable nylon knobs and a compressible rubber center lined with nubs and grooves which can be filled with your dog’s favorite spreadable treat, such as peanut butter or cheese. The included dental support treats help to clean teeth and freshen breath while your dog chews the day away, and the ends unscrew so rawhide treat rings can be replaced again and again. Even better, this toy is dishwasher-safe to keep it clean and ready for the next playful adventure.', '(4) Sportsmen Rawhide Refill Treats', 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. Supervised play will help toys last longer and most importantly keep your pal safe. No dog toy is truly indestructible, so always remove the toy from playtime if pieces begin to break off.', 'For Sportsmen Refill Treats: Click Here', '

                        See all items by PetSafe
']
key_benefits: ['This toy includes durable nylon knobs and a compressible rubber center lined with nubs and grooves.', 'Nubs help stimulate gums and clean teeth while your pup enjoys his toy.', 'Includes six rawhide rings which help clean teeth and freshen breath as your dog chews.', 'The ends unscrew so you can replace the treats again and again.', 'This toy is dishwasher-safe to keep it clean and ready for playtime.']
reviews: [My dog loves to chew on nylon bones, antlers, etc. I bought this because I thought she could use more of a challenge and she loves meaty treats. I was wrong. It was a waste of money. She just looks confused at it when I give it to her. Looking at the toy myself, I'm not even sure how a dog is supposed to remove the rawhide discs. I even tried giving her one of the rawhide discs on it own so it wouldn't be a complete loss, but she won't touch it either. Unfortunately, I do not recommend this product., This was bought as a replacement for the PetSafe Sportsmen Bristle Bone Dog Toy because the bristles came out immediately. (NOT SAFE!) This product has no bristles and so far is holding up great! My 7 lb Maltese absolutely loves chew toys and rawhides, and the bone and rubber nubs make her work for it. She can take down a normal rawhide chew in 5 minutes or less, but this keeps her occupied for much longer, even though the actual rawhide is smaller. She is so much happier now. Thank you, Chewy!, This toy did not last 30 min from the time it was taken out of the wrapper. I have an aggressive chewer but it sure did not make it very long. I would recommend if you have a non-aggressive chewer. I sure wanted it to work for my boy - but don't rule it out for your puppy if you don't have a toy destroy monster like mine! I think the concept it great! Good luck, My 40 pound beagle mix is an aggressive chewer. She can destroy a red Kong toy. But she loves this toy and it keeps her busy for awhile. Not sure how to rate it.This is the 2nd one I've bought because somehow my dog got the knob off one end and chewed up the threaded shaft. But she loves it and it is relatively inexpensive. Supervision is recommended. We'll see how long this one lasts, This product is way to easy for an aggressive chewers to get the treats out of. The middle ring is all soft plastic which does not hold the treats securely. My cattledog/staffy mix had the treats out in less then a minute and she is uninterested in continuing to chew on it once treats are gone. This product would be great for teething puppies and smaller less aggressive chewers., My son's dog usually destroys a toy in one day. This one survived his last visit without any issues! It kept him busy for a long time too. I'm ordering more of the rawhide rings for his next visit., I have heard many good things about this toy! But, sadly mine takes it apart everytime he gets his mouth on it..., My fur baby loves this toy. She is 10 lbs and this is a good size for her. She loves it. She plays with it every day, My golden lab loved this toy but dropped it while carrying it around and the end knob broke off with the stem threads inside it. Now, I can't add the rawhide ring and use the toy any more. Wish the end were a rubber material instead of plastic., This seems to be a toy that will hold up... My dog likes it even without the rawhide rings. I'll report back and let everyone know how long it lasts.]

reviews: [My pup is not a chewer, she is usually a lover of all her toys. This one she could care less about. It is heavy and lifeless., Love it! The toy is well made and my only request is that I have two boxers and need two DIFFERENT COLORS so they know which one is theirs. NOT THAT THAT MATTERS, ha ha!, I bought this toy for my aggressive chewer 60# lab. This toy was terrible. My lab literally started chewing on this right away and after a few minutes pieces were already coming off. Not worth the money., Bought this for my bulldog because she is always taking off with my husband's paint brushes. She picked it up twice when it first arrived but has nothing to do with it since., I got this thinking it was going to be TUFF to match it's RUFF title. It lasted literally less than 10 minutes before the corner was nearly chewed off.....VERY disappointed, Looked true to picture unfortunately it is not for heavy chewers within a few minutes my American bully had broken chunks off. The one I received is yellow with green splatters, Bought for my Husky, hoping to add to her collection (So far only kongs in 3 sizes) of toys that would last a week, hopefully more. Within 5 minutes she had already chewed it to pieces. Would have rather spent $11 on another Kong., You may want to avoid this toy if your dog is anything like mine.. here are pictures of what my Corso mix did in less than 5 minutes. I threw it out because I don't want to worry about him swallowing the pieces.. He is only a puppy and did this..]

reviews: [I thought this would have been a good long-term interactive chew toy for my dog. I was wrong. It lasted 1 time, the rubber is not sturdy by any means. By the time my dog was figuring out how to get the treats I stuffed in it, out. It was crumbling all over., Couldn't find the snacks to slide on the toy. descriptions:

This bone-shaped toy features a unique spiky texture that helps massage gums with every fetch and a loud squeaker inside for extra excitement. It can stand up to extra-tough play and has been bite tested for up to 150 pounds, although it’s soft and gentle on doggy gums, even for teething puppies. Since it’s made out of food-grade, BPA-free TPR rubber, it’s safe, non-toxic and perfect for everyday play in the yard, at home, or at the park! Plus, they come in an assortment of bright colors and different sizes to suit your pal’s size and bite.', 'Ships in a variety of random and fun colors!', 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. ']
key_benefits: ['Interactive dog toy with loud squeaker inside and unique spiky texture.', 'Made of BPA-free, food-grade TPR rubber so it’s safe to play with every day.', 'Can stand up to tough play and chewing since it’s bite-tested for up to 150 pounds.', 'Spiky texture massages gums with every fetch and it’s great for teething puppies.', 'Perfect for small and medium dogs, and is available in different bright colors and sizes.']
reviews: [Our boy loves playing ball, but I thought this was cute and it’s the same texture as his favorite ball so I decided to try it. He loves it! It’s not as easy to catch as the ball but I think he likes the challenge., I have a 20lb mini Aussie Shepherd and he hates this toy. I bought it a few months ago and he hasn’t even touched it. I’ve tried throwing it so he might want to play with it but he’s actually scared of it and he runs away from the toy. If you have a bigger dog maybe they’ll like it but since it has weird spikes, most dogs won’t even touch it. Was a waste of money and I would not buy this again., We were excited to give this toy to our dog, as the description says it was tested for rough play. Yet after 10 minutes the toy proved to be weak. It was destroyed to pieces. I do not recommend this., My 24 pound dog acted like this toy hurt his teeth when he tried to chew it. He stopped being interested it it quickly. I guess I should have bought a smaller size., My puppy loves to play fetch with this ! It helps provide her with needed excersize ! She loves the bumpy feel ,it feels good since she’s teething!, My dog loves the spiked texture, strong bounce, and the squeaker. It has been very durable so far. I'm more impressed than I expected to be., She loves chewing on this adorable bone. She also brings it to me for me to brush her with it. It's so cute. Definitely would buy again., Absolutely blown away by the durability of this toy! While the squeaker didn’t last long (which I’m not at all mad about), the toy has withstood a heavy chewer (our golden retriever) and is my cocker spaniel’s favorite toy in the whole world. He doesn’t like to do anything without it and goes into panic mode when he can’t find it. Great toy for playing fetch as well., We bought our huge boxer mix a bunch of toys for Christmas, and this was one of them. Almost 6 months later, it’s one of only 2 still standing! He’s so rough on toys that they often don’t even last a day. This toy was cheap so I figured why not try it. He spends hours picking at the little spikes with his teeth, and he’s obsessed with it! The squeak is solid and strong. Just can’t believe how longs it’s lasted., My dog had it in pieces within 10 minutes. Luckily she doesn’t swallow the pieces so it just made a mess. Would not purchase again.]

Want to extend play time? And to add some extra fun into the mix, this toy can be stuffed with KONG’s Stuff’N Easy Treat, Snacks or Ziggies (sold separately) or any of her favorite rewards like peanut butter, yogurt or kibble!", 'Every dog plays differently and, since not all toys are created equal, it’s always best to keep a close watch on your pup in case things get ruff. ']
key_benefits: ['Made in the USA from globally sourced materials.', "Perfect for stuffing with KONG Stuff'N Easy Treat Paste and Snacks for longer-lasting play.", 'Relied upon by veterinarians, trainers, and dog enthusiasts for over 40 years.', 'Provides play, helps reduce boredom, and relieves separation anxiety.', 'Unpredictable bounce for virtually unlimited games of fetch, even while you’re away.']
reviews: [I got the small Kong classic for my Westie. She’s 10 months old and still likes to chew. I bought the peanut butter filler to go with it. I originally loved it at first because she was distracted for a good two hours while I worked (I froze the toy with the peanut butter filler inside). She got all of the filling out and was chewing on the toy and managed to chew off the top half and this was the first day I gave it to her. I’m going to try the Kong extreme chew and see if it’s any better., Very few brands can survive my dog's teeth for more than 3 days, as a mix of many breeds including German Shepherd and Staffy. Phoebe loves her Kongs, and they're perfect to give to her during a storm to calm her down. Bonus points if you freeze the filling! It doesn't take her very long to get it cleaned out, but she LOVES when I take it out and starts offering all of her tricks to get it as quickly as possible., Not sure why I waited so long to get one of these. I moistened my GSD's kibble & stuffed it inside, then froze it. It kept her busy & occupied for a full hour! Great toy & appreciate that it keeps her busy, mentally stimulated, & out of trouble. I bought 3 more (black extreme version this time) to ensure I always have some in the freezer., My 3 month puppy absolutely loves this toy, as do my partner and I. We like to fill this with his wet dog food, freeze it and then let him play with it when we need to keep him busy. This toy allows us both to work from home--taking Zoom meetings undistracted! This toy is very durable and strong, exactly what a teething puppy needs. I can't recommend this toy enough., All of my dogs love/loved this toy. They get excited each and every single time with give it to them daily. It allows them some challenges to get to their treat which gives them some positive stimulation. They hold up for a long time as well. Just make sure you choose the Kong best for your dogs age and size., I filled it with treats and she was busy for a while then she gets really tired with all the licking. I got the medium one and to me it is soo tiny. My puppy is medium sized and is about 35 pounds. I expected it to be a lot larger but the measurements are correct so I would recommend going a size up for more fun. I used a tennis ball to compare the size of the medium kong, There are 6 Kongs in rotation at all times in my house. They can be filled with wet puppy food and frozen. Some can be filled with broken cookie pieces awaiting use during a Zoom meeting or used to get us to a meal. And there are a couple freshly emptied. She loves them., My two foster puppies, Cosmo and Cleo, absolutely LOVED these toys and were deliriously happy when I filled them with the peanut butter filling. They were kept happy and amused for hours and the Kong was the best teething toy ever!, I haven't given this to my dog as yet. He has a lot of toys to play with but when I see a toy failing this will be given to him. I've use this at my Service Dog Campus and it was used a lot there. Keeps the dog very active., My dog LOVES this. Keeps her busy for when I’m leaving for a little while. The only down side is if something is left in there it is a little bit of a hassle to get out or the inserts (the ones that kong makes specifically for them) breaks off into it, it is verrrry hard to get it out. Other than that I love this product for her!]

title: Nylabone Strong Chew Stick Maple Bacon Flavored Dog Chew Toy
descriptions:
['Help fulfill your dog’s natural chewing instincts with Nylabone’s Strong Maple Bacon Chew Stick! This toy is made of durable nylon and real wood that has been infused with a drool-worthy maple bacon flavor your dog will love! Nylabone’s patented over-mold technology is what makes this toy look and even feel like real bark. Think of it as the modern version of a regular branch—that means no unsafe splintering and no dirty mess. As your pal chews to his heart’s content, the toy’s texture and maple bacon flavor will work to help clean his teeth and freshen his breath.', '

                        See all items by Nylabone
']
key_benefits: ["Real wood and a strong nylon chew toy won't splinter and serves as a safe alternative to real sticks.", 'Infused with a tail-wagging maple bacon flavor throughout the entire toy.', 'Helps to remove plaque and tartar and encourage fresh breath as your dog chews.', 'Life-like bark texture helps satisfies your dog’s natural urge to chew.', 'Available in two sizes, so dogs from all barks of life can enjoy this unique toy.']
reviews: [We weren’t sure about this bone, but it is a favorite of our pups! So much so that they will argue over it and I’ve had to start buying two at a time!! The only thing is because they love on it so much they whittle it down to nothing pretty fast and we have to really watch for when it gets to small so we can throw it out because I’m afraid it will get stuck in their throats. Also, pick it up every night, this is worse than stepping on a lego!, Our new German Shepherd pup wanted to chew every stick and rock in the yard so I hoped this would meet her need to chew and be so much healthier. SHE LOVES THIS! Since opening the package she has not stopped chewing on it., Both dogs love the chew sticks. We got them because one dog likes to chase sticks in the yard. We thought we could throw this toy and she would chase it. I think the flavoring distracts her. They will both lay in front of the couch and chew them., We have a stick connuseur when she's outside, and she loves this toy so she can continue to chew on a stick inside, too! The large size is perfect for her to grab tight with her legs and chew till her her heart's content., Poor quality. My dog started to eat The bone in a matter of minutes and pieces of it were falling off. Had to throw away within 15 minutes of having it. Might be good for a small dog for my lab it did not work., I bought this cause I have an 8mth old Rottweiler who has teeth still coming in in the back. This was actually the first one I had came across that said Souper & wolf for some reason I thought that was make them tougher. & She absolutely loves sticks so I thought this wld be perfect. She did choose it over another bone that I had but it had pieces coming off of it in less than a day or two. To make sure she's not swallowing & gets hurt I had to take it away from her. I knew there wld be ware & tare I just didn't expect it to be so early., This particular item lasted less than 30 seconds out of the box before it was in chunks on the floor and had to be thrown away. The traditional nylabone is 1 million times better and lasts my pup normally over 4 months. I would stick to the traditional for the future., Khan loves this and doesn't readily share it with his sister, so that's saying something. He usually isn't protective of his chew toys. He carried it around all day yesterday. It seems to stand up well to his power chewing -- he's part GSD and pittie, so he can chew. It doesn't leave a mess., My guys wanna bring sticks in and this is a great toy for them. The texted on it looks like a stick and they like to chew. My 4 year old has put some dents on the end but has not broken peace’s off yet. Only bad thing is it can get sharp from the parts where they chew and makes me worry they will cut their gums if not watched., Stick? Yes! Playing fetch? Yup! Chew toy? Excellent! Park friends? Total win. A mini puppy fight broke out over this toy- that’s how great this toy is- resource guarding became necessary. (No toys or puppies were harmed in the making of this review) We even sent it home with her bestie for his neutering surgery so he had something to chew. Win.]

reviews: [Buy this. Yes, yes, yes. My pup is 8 months (50 lbs) and love to destroy toys. He adores this. The first time I took it out of the package, I put some PB inside the wheel and then rolled it. He chased it, pounced on it, and then proceeded to spend the next 45 min chewing on it! Longest he's sat in one place with a toy before. We've had it for 4 days and each morning he goes to look for it. The 3 level chubby kong and other toys are abandoned, he is going for this. I stick a treat in it once in a while and he has to really work to get it out- he loves it. Easy to carry around, not too heavy, and he can chew to his heart's content. I wish I bought it 5 months ago., The most durable toy my 9 month Bernese pup has had to date. She shreds rope toys and soft toys and has taken chunks out of rubber toys but this was one of the highest rated "indestructible" toys so we gave it a shot and it is her FAVORITE. Only downside is it is a little small but she still loves it. Not even a dent in it and she's had it for a couple weeks. If you throw the toy overhand then it rolls across the whole yard and gives her good exercise chasing it. I recommend this toy to all my neighbors with puppies that chew a lot. I think it's the perfect balance of being flexible and more rigid so the toy never breaks., I bought the medium/large version of this tire for two 60-70 pounds labs. it’s smaller than my hand, which is a lot smaller than their last medium/large tire. Both my dogs still love playing with it, but I was hoping it would be larger cause they like to play tug of war with tires. This one is too small for them to do that., I have a pair of Belgian Malinois and they're pretty strong chewers. I purchased this Large KONG tire expecting they would have a great time with a new toy. I received it via FedEx today, and it's roughly about the size of a plain donut that you'd get from Dunkin Donuts. If you have a large dog, or heavy chewer....I wouldn't recommend this product., I got this for my 5 year old pitty mix who chews through every toy you’d find at the pet store except nylabones! Like the title says, it’s smaller than I expected and I got the medium/large size. He was playing with it pretty hard yesterday and chewing up a storm, but still looks brand new- no teeth marks or anything! Will definitely buy this again!, Wow, this is really tiny for a large I thought it would be so much bigger. My 60 plus dog doesn’t quite know what to do with it. It was a replacement for one about 6”. I bought it because I love all of Kong’s products., My Grizzwald ~ 60lbs, loves all of his Kong Extreme toys and this one is no different! I purchased the MED/LG size tire. It's smaller than expected however it's perfect because he is petite for his breed. Keep in mind no toy is indestructible. He has managed to nibble bits off of his Kong Extreme ball (see picture), little by little however it has taken him about a year to do so and he gnaws on it 24/7. He's happy to know that a new ball is expected to arrive with his next auto shipment, he loves delivery day!, Although smaller than I thought the girls love this toy. Since then, I actually found some that were larger and has a pull rope, which is great for two pups. This is one toy they did not tear up. Yeah, Our 73lb bully mix can destroy anything we give him. But this, he cant even bite through it. Usually anything rubber we buy, he can bite holes all in it. But not this one. It was worth the money., I have a 1.5 year old, 125 lb. Lab/Great Pyrenees mix...and he is a MAJOR chewer. He loves this tire, and hasn't been able to destroy it yet, even after several months. I only buy Kong toys for him, and have had very good luck with them.]

reviews: [I was excited that when I gave this toy to my dog that he loved it. Was seemingly able to do what all other toys have failed to do: pass the Rigsby test. But I noticed in the morning he was slowly nibbling away pieces of the ends. I was wondering if it was ok for his stomach. The toy brown colored puke on the carpet gave me my answer. Another toy goes down :(, I wanted to get this for our power chewer as the one we had similar to this lasted quite awhile. I do not reccomend this for anyone who has an aggressive or semi aggresive chewer gave this to our dog and in less than 30mins she had bitten pieces off an was trying to swallow it, we immediately threw it out . Will not buy again., I have 4 dogs, 2 cockatiel’s and a cat. 2 of my dogs are German Shepherds and they chew through everything in a matter of minutes. These bones keep them occupied for weeks or months and happy!!! And believe me I have tried many this one is by far the best!!, I bought this because it said it was a tough chew toy. I had to take it away from my dog less than an hour after to giving it to him because he had chewed off little pieces that were everywhere and I was worried he would swallow them., I have two dogs. They would trick one another into dropping it and taking their eye off of it to go sneak it away. I decided to buy a second one. They love these things. Their teeth are beautifully white. They have served for hours and hours of chewing. They can hold it so easily., Both dogs love this chew toy and I will purchase more soon. The doxie, carries it into our bed, and guards it all night. The pug loves to chew and lick this bone and it's the right size for him to pick up and take to his favorite places to relax for a good chew., I bought 2 different bones and my dogs love them. I would buy this again. They love the bacon and fight over who will have the first chew of the day., I bought this hoping for a better alternative to nylabones, as our dog is a strong chewer and ends up chewing away a lot of the material (and swallowing a lot of it I am sure). The description heavily mentions the fact that this is made with bamboo fiber. I completely missed the sidebar that mentions it's polypropylene (plastic) and bamboo. It feels mostly plastic. After having this less than a week, our 55lb dog has completely gnawed down one of the "bone" ends and probably swallowed a lot of plastic. He really enjoys the texture of this, being a bit softer than our xl nylabone, but if you are concerned about your dog ingesting plastic - this may not be the toy for you., I got this for my big boy and he loves it!!! He was confused at first because it’s not his regular bone (I usually re purchase a nylabone for him annually) but after a couple minutes he loved it!, My dogs lower jaw got caught in the bone after minimal use. The other wishbone style bones have a larger space. He is a puggle.]
